title: low calorie chocolate cream pie
directions: In large microwave-safe bowl, stir together sugar, cornstarch and cocoa; gradually stir in milk.
Microwave at High 2 minutes; stir well.
Microwave at High 2 to 5 minutes or until mixture just begins to boil; stir well.
Microwave at High 30 seconds to 1 minute until mixture is very hot and thickened.
Pour into crust. Place plastic directly onto surface; refrigerate several hours or until firm.
Garnish with whipped topping and fresh fruit, if desired.

title: divinity
directions: In saucepan, mix the sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Slowly bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Cook to 50 on candy scale (in between soft and hard stage).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually pour hot syrup into whites, beating constantly.
Beat until candy begins to hold its shape.
Beat in vanilla and powdered sugar.
(This amount of powdered sugar makes a real improvement in texture.)
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper, or pour into buttered pan.
Let stand several minutes until firm.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 50 pieces.

title: snack time molasses cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses. Blend.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Blend in coconut and walnuts. Drop by level teaspoons 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In soup pot, put onion and sear it, then add taco seasoning and chilies.
Add chicken broth and tomatoes (squish them with fingers).
Add corn and cooked meat.
Bring to a boil.
Add cilantro.

title: sausage treat
directions: Unroll and spread crescent rolls in pan.
Brown sausage and drain.
Crumble sausage over rolls.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage. Beat eggs (salt and pepper if desired).
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: eggplant from the border
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and set aside.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach and wrap in paper towels.
Let stand while mixing in all other ingredients.
Mix well and fold in spinach.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut out top of round French bread.
Pull out insides; cut into bite size pieces for dipping.
Put dip in hollowed out bread crust.
Can be made the day before.

title: open house punch
directions: Combine punch, citrus juice and strawberries.
Mix well.
Stir in soda.
Add punch cubes.
Garnish with orange slices and serve. Makes 22 four ounce servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove from bones.
Tear into chunks.
Layer chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread 1 can cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Microwave 1 medium onion in 3 or 4 tablespoons margarine for 5 minutes.
Mix onion with a small package of Pepperidge Farm bread crumbs.
Add this to top of chicken.
Pour 3 cups of broth over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets until tender. Blanch with cold water and the skins will slip off. Make syrup by boiling together water, vinegar, sugar and salt. Add a few whole cloves to boiling syrup, but leave them out of the beets as they tend to leave dark spots. Add a pinch of black pepper. Bring syrup to a good boil and add slices or whole beets. Bring to boil again and put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: In a quart-size glass measuring cup or bowl, place oil, onions and garlic.
Cook, uncovered, at Medium power (50%) for 1 minute. Add tomatoes, oregano and basil and cook, uncovered, at High power (100%) for 10 minutes.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese, spinach and beans.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo; add chocolate chips and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over Crispix and blend until coated.
Shake in bag (clean plastic) with powdered sugar until coated.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Whip powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: marble pudding cake(mom or dad will help with the hard parts.)
directions: Preheat oven and prepare cake according to box directions. Bake in a 13 x 9 baking pan. While cake is baking, prepare pudding.

title: zippy jalapeno dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: blueberry tea muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt together.
Sprinkle blueberries with remaining flour.
Mix lightly and bake at 400° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Simmer hamburg, sausage, green pepper, onion, celery and green olives.
Add the mushrooms, soup, sauce and oregano.
Add noodles. Bake covered 1/2 hour at 350°.
Remove and sprinkle on pizza cheese and bake uncovered 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in greased Pyrex casserole dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until firm and lightly browned (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Serves 16 to 20.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
In a large greased casserole, combine all ingredients and stir to mix. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, covered, and 1/2 hour, uncovered. Serves 4 to 6.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks beating good.
Add pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Line a baking dish or pan with whole graham crackers and pour the mixture on the crackers, then spread the stiffly beaten egg whites on top of mixture.
Place another layer of crackers on top of the egg whites.
Pour partially set jello on the egg whites.
Put the pan in refrigerator until jello sets.
Before serving, add whipped cream on top.

title: surprise salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple and sugar. Add and mix well the jello and water.
Set until quite thick.
Fold in the whipped cream, walnuts and cheese.
Set until firm.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut into bite sized pieces.
Mix all ingredients and put in a large casserole or baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and slivered almonds.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Yummy.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges; mix with cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Sprinkle dry jello over mixture;
mix well.
Refrigerate a while before serving.

title: make ahead barbecue
directions: Put meat in roaster.
Mix onion, sugar, mustard, pepper, vinegar, water, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour over meat.
Cover.
Cook in a 325° oven for 5 to 6 hours until meat is very tender (falls off the bone).
Let meat and drippings become cold.
Remove all fat.
Chop meat and reheat in sauce.
May be frozen.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Break 5 soda crackers into blender. Cover and run on speed 4 (low) until finely crumbled.
Empty into bowl. Repeat process for remaining crackers (1/2 cup crumbs).
Put nuts in blender; cover and run on low until chopped.
Add to cracker crumbs.
Put chocolate chips in blender. Cover and run on low until fine. Add to crumbled mixture.
Beat egg whites with an electric mixer until they form soft peaks. Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, continuing to beat until stiff but not dry.
Fold into crumb mixture and add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets. Bake 12 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend.	Let
stand
at least one hour.	Can be prepared the day before.
Keeps well.
Serve with your favorite vegetables and chips.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together chicken, celery, green pepper, walnuts and onion.
In small bowl, stir together mayonnaise, cream and vinegar.
Add to chicken and toss well.
Chill several hours before serving.
Serve on croissants!

title: meat ball stew
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, thyme, egg and garlic; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 20 meat balls.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook meat balls until browned on all sides.
Pour off fat.
Stir soup and water into skillet; stir in potatoes, carrots and onion.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, adding more water, if needed.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Freeze.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Crumble bacon; add bacon, cheese, onion, pepper and mushrooms in pie shell. Beat eggs, half and half, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until done.

title: 7-up fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and 7-Up. Chill until slightly thick.
Add bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until firm in a large pan.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: crepes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour 1/4 cup batter onto hot griddle and swirl to make a thin pancake.
Flip and serve hot with your favorite jelly or jam.

title: chocolate peanut butter clusters
directions: Combine both packages of morsels in 8-cup glass dish. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir.
Repeat in 1 minute cycles until melted (usually 3 minutes).
Remove and stir in peanuts. Drop onto wax paper by spoonfuls.
Yields 4 dozens.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Saute onion in margarine; add mushroom soup and cheese and heat slowly.
Add drained broccoli and mushrooms.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: chocolate or peanut butter microwave fudge
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter or chocolate chips in microwave oven on High power for 2 minutes.
Remove.
Add vanilla; stir well.
Add powdered sugar, a little at a time, until mixed well. Press mixture into a 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Freeze for 10 minutes. Cut into squares and serve.

title: german slaw
directions: Bring to a boil the celery seed, vinegar, salad oil, sugar and salt and pour over the cabbage, onion, pepper and pimiento mixture. Let set in a tightly covered container for 12 hours. Stir well and serve.
Good with fish.

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Place vegetables in bowl.
Make dressing by mixing sugar, olive oil, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
The longer it sits, the better it gets.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add peanut butter and powdered sugar. Cream well and fold in topping.
Pile in baked and cooled graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle top with peanuts.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: potato supreme
directions: Defrost potatoes. Combine next 7 ingredients with the potatoes in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Saute corn flake crumbs in 1/4 cup melted butter and spread on top of potato mixture. Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Casserole should be bubbling on sides.

title: filled tortillas
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on tortillas and roll up. Chill and cut into 1-inch pieces. Serve with Mexican hot sauce or picante sauce.

title: scampi on the grill
directions: Mix all ingredients together except shrimp (this is the marinade).
Place 8 to 10 shrimp on each skewer.
Marinate skewered shrimp 2 hours or longer.
Preheat grill.
Baste shrimp with marinade left.
Cook until done.

title: linguine in red clam sauce
directions: *Drain one can of clams; reserve liquid from the other.

title: e z cream puffs
directions: Split cookies and set aside.
Drain pineapple.
Beat the cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Add pineapple; mix.
Fill bottom of each cookie and cap loosely with top.
Refrigerate until needed. They taste better when they have set for several hours.

title: louisiana yam corn bread
directions: Sift the flour with the corn meal, baking powder, salt and sugar and set aside.
Combine the eggs, milk and oil in a large bowl; beat until smooth.
Add the yams; beat until blended.
Add flour mixture; stir only until the flour mixture is moist.
Spoon into 2 greased 8-inch square pans.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix chicken, soups, onion and Ro-Tel.
Layer with tortillas. Grate cheese and put all over top.
Pour Ro-Tel over cheese and top with tortillas. Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Spray 2-quart baking dish with Pam. Cook grits according to package directions. Remove from heat and add cheese and butter. Stir until melted. Add eggs; blend well. Pour into dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and onion in saucepan; bring to a boil. Drain.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Bake at 300°.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar with the ground cranberries while making the jello. When the jello begins to set, gently stir in the above ingredients.

title: caramel crackers
directions: Spread crackers and peanuts on cookie sheet.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes. Pour over crackers and stir.
Bake in preheated oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: strawberry and pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into 13 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix jello, boiling water and strawberries; stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Pour cooled jello on top and refrigerate.
Let set for 4 to 5 hours.
Can top with more Cool Whip.

title: good-for-you cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together and stir in the next 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook to a hard ball. Peanuts will begin to pop before done. Add soda. Stir very quickly. Pour onto cookie sheet. Do not disturb until cool.

title: family-style casserole
directions: Step 1:
Place frozen beef and tomato sauce in a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid.

title: chicken cheese dip
directions: Mix soups, mayonnaise and cream cheese together in saucepan. Stir over low heat until liquified. Add chicken, salt, pepper and green onions. Pour ingredients into casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with Fritos. Enjoy!!!

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix in flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
(Mixes best in food processor or blender.)
Add chocolate chips, chocolate bar and nuts.

title: mexican crescent ring
directions: Brown ground beef;

drain. Add taco seasoning. Heat oven according to crescent roll package. On round baking stone (or greased round pan), unroll 8 crescent rolls; divide into triangles. Make circle with short side in center and points sticking out. Make second circle; match short sides to first 8 with these points to the inside. Spoon ground beef mixture where 2 circles meet. Top with cheese; fold points up over meat from center and outside. Bake per roll instructions plus about 3 to 4 minutes, until rolls are brown.

title: johnson's hot rolls
directions: Blend oleo, sugar, egg, yeast and salt.
Add water and flour. Knead.
Let rise 1 hour.
Make into rolls and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and salt.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together and alternate with buttermilk into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, mixing well. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: swedish cocoa balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, add cocoa, coffee, flavoring and rolled oats.
Chill until cold, then roll in small balls in palms of hands, pressing firmly.
These are not baked.
Yields about 36.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Put bread cubes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter and pour over bread cubes; toss lightly.
Heat tomato puree with water and brown sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over bread and toss.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Drop into hot tomato sauce and cook about 2 hours.
Makes 10 to 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Butter 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Mix all together and pour in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beaumodine dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Prepare the day before.

title: crock-pot venison
directions: Flour and season the roast with pepper, salt and garlic. Cook until tender.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix flour, pudding, egg, milk and butter until doughy.
Put in pie pan.
Drain peaches and place on dough.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons of peach juice and put on top of peaches. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no cook cherry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill 2 pie crusts with mixture.

title: raisin creme pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook on top of stove until thickens.
Put in crust; cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Mix together first 6 ingredients. Add muffin mix (always use Jiffy).
Pour into well-greased pan or baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jeanne's pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time and mix until smooth.
Sift flour with soda, salt and nutmeg, then gradually add to creamed mixture.
If batter is too thick, add some of the pineapple juice.
Add pineapple before using up all of the flour; this will keep the batter from becoming too thin.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350° to 375° or until lightly browned.
Frost with a glaze when cooled and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave rice krispie treats
directions: Rub margarine stick on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place margarine in a large bowl.
Microwave on High for 45 seconds.
Add marshmallows.
Stir.
Microwave 1 minute.
Stir.
Microwave 45 seconds.
Add cereal.
Stir.
Pat into pan.
Let cool.

title: russian cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in flour, one cup at a time. Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: bara brith fruit bread(a recipe from wales)
directions: Place the fruit and sugar in a mixing bowl and soak overnight in the strained tea.
Sieve the flour and mixed spice and warm the marmalade.
Add the flour, warm marmalade and beaten egg to the soaked fruit.
Mix well; pour the mixture into a greased loaf tin. Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Cool on a wire rack.
Serve sliced and buttered.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Food process hearts, well mashed.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spread into 1-quart baking dish (lightly greased or sprayed).
Bake for 1/2 hour at 400° until top is lightly brown. Cut bread into individual bite sized pieces to spread dip onto. Spread dip onto bread with knife and enjoy.

title: beef tips and gravy
directions: Brown beef cubes in margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over rice.

title: chinese meal
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger.
Fix spaghetti as directed. Over medium heat, place carrots, cabbage and onion.
Blend in hamburger and spaghetti.
Season with soy sauce.

title: caramel pie
directions: Cook in double boiler the 3/4 cup of sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk. Caramelize 1 cup of sugar until rich brown. Add butter or oleo. Pour into other mixture. Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue made from egg whites.
Use 1 tablespoon of sugar to each egg white.

title: meatballs(portuguese)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make meatballs.
Fry or bake the meatballs.
Add them to sauce.

title: chili meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 6 ingredients with 1/4 c. of the tomato juice.
Shape into 18 balls.
Arrange in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish and pour over the remaining 3/4 c. of tomato juice.
Cover and bake 1 hour, adding more juice if necessary.

title: taco salad
directions: Put lettuce in the bottom of a large bowl.
Add in order listed, green onions, tomatoes, chili beans, and cheese.
Punch holes in the bag of Fritos and crush them with your hands, add to salad.
Just before serving pour dressing over all and toss real good.
This can be made ahead of time and
Fritos and dressing added just before serving.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put into a casserole dish.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 300°.
Do not peek.
Serve on egg noodles or rice.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Let simmer in a saucepan, after mixing all ingredients, except hot dogs, for 20 minutes.
Add cut to bite-size pieces of hot dogs to sauce and simmer 30 more minutes.
Great in crock-pot.

title: hot sauce marinade for beef or chicken
directions: Mix marinade the night before and shake a few times.
Marinate chicken for 8 hours in the refrigerator.
Marinate the beef for 8 hours in the refrigerator and 8 hours at room temperature.

title: cranberry mince pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; add water.
Over high heat, cook and stir until boiling.
Add cranberries; return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: tuna sauce with pasta
directions: Combine garlic, parsley and basil.
Set aside 1/2 of the mixture.
In a medium saucepan, saute other 1/2 of the mixture in oil (do not brown).
Add red pepper and salt.
Cook 1 minute.
Add tuna and tomato paste.
Stir with wooden spoon 1 minute more.
Add wine and stir over high heat until paste is dissolved.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes more.
Adjust seasonings to taste. Remove from heat and add remaining herb mixture.
Pour over hot cooked pasta.
Serves 4 as a main dish.

title: beef wellington
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat the clarified butter in a frying pan over medium heat.
Add the beef to the hot butter, searing it on all sides.
Season with salt and pepper and remove from the pan. Coat the filet of beef with Mushroom Pate.
Set aside.

title: microwave spaghetti squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise. Scoop out seeds and place, cut side down, in microwave-safe dish.
Add 1/3 cup water.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender, turning dish after 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Use a fork to remove spaghetti-like strands.
Yields 2 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add spices, eggs and vanilla; mix.
Add flour, baking powder and soda; mix.
Add pumpkin; mix.
Add nuts; mix.
Pour into 3 greased and floured coffee cans.
Fill half full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from cans when cool. Slice and serve.

title: kay's barbecue
directions: Place roast in crock-pot with 1/2 onion on top and 1/2 on bottom.
Cover with water.
Cook 12 hours or overnight.
Drain liquid; debone and chop up roast.
Remove fat.
Place chopped meat back into crock-pot with barbecue sauce; simmer on low for several hours.

title: curried pecans
directions: Marinate cooked shrimp in Italian dressing for several hours in the refrigerator.
Drain and arrange on picks with pitted ripe olives.

title: lemon sponge cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar together until fluffy. Beat in egg yolks, flour, salt, milk, lemon peel and juice.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 375° oven that was preheated for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 45 minutes longer or until top is golden and pick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Serves 8.

title: baked shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice mushrooms and saute slowly in butter. Mix lightly with shrimp, rice and cheese.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onion, celery and mushrooms. Saute.
Pour over bread cubes in large mixing bowl; add all seasoning.
Mix eggs with broth and add to mix.
Pack in crock-pot but do not stir.
Cook on High 45 minutes, then on Low for 4 to 8 hours.

title: bride's dinner
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and shape into four balls.
Place four pork chops in shallow baking pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place 1 ball of stuffing on each.
Core apples and set in pan with chops.
Combine sugar, raisins and cinnamon and fill center of apples.
Roll sweet potatoes in melted butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper and place in pan with chops.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in all ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon into baking dish; top with cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add banana, oats, egg and nuts.

title: chana halwa
directions: Cook yellow split peas with the half and half on low heat until tender.
Blend together.

title: pecan macaroons
directions: Beat the eggs just enough to mix them, then stir all other ingredients together until well mixed.
Drop by small spoonfuls on well-greased pans, allowing room between each one. Bake in a very slow oven and do not attempt to take the cakes up until they are cold.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(the pie that does the impossible by making its crust.)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/2-inch or 10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat all ingredients until smooth, about 2 minutes. Pour into plate.
Bake 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Dip fork in flour and push down. Can put red cinnamon hots in center.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: almond spritz
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.	Add egg and beat well.	Sift flour and gradually add into creamed mixture. Stir in almond flavoring.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
Fill cookie press and press cookies onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: dad's favorite strawberry meringue kisses
directions: To prepare individual meringue shells, have egg whites at room temperature in a small mixing bowl.
Combine first 4 ingredients. Cover large baking sheet with plain ungreased brown paper or with kitchen parchment.
Draw 8 circles, 3 1/2-inches in diameter. Spread each with about 1/3 cup of meringue.
Using back of spoon, shape into shells.
Form a hollow in center.
Bake meringues at 275° for 1 hour.
Turn off heat and let dry in oven (door closed) about 1 hour.
Fill with vanilla ice cream and top with fresh or frozen strawberries.

title: baklava
directions: Prepare Honey Syrup and set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix salad dressing, 1 cup water, melted oleo and stuffing mix. Beat well; add eggs, milk, chicken, celery, salt , pepper, onion and carrot.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend soup and milk.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ziti and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute garlic salt in butter.
Cook and drain ziti.
Add chicken broth to garlic and butter mixture, then add frozen broccoli and bring to a boil. Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over drained ziti in a casserole dish.
Cut up chicken breast and add to mixture.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Put in oven and bake at 350° until cheese melts slightly.
Serve hot.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour apple cider into percolator; place candies in percolator basket. Cover and begin the perking cycle. When cycle is complete, remove the basket and leave punch in the pot to keep warm.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Open date and put nut in center. Close date over nuts.
In small bowl or plastic Ziploc bag, put 1/2 cup sugar. Roll dates in sugar, then place in airtight container.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in pan sprayed with Pam. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
This makes large pan of bread and is very good with beans.

title: gingersnaps
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine about 1/2 of the flour and all of the remaining ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer on medium to high speed until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour by hand. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in the blender until smooth. Refrigerate at least 2 hours and serve with crudites.

title: fruit balls
directions: Grind fruit and mix together well.
Chop nuts and mix.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut in that order into a well-greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Mix cake mix according to package directions. Pour over coconut and nuts. Combine remaining ingredients; beat until smooth and dollop over cake. DO NOT SPREAD. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool; turn out on serving tray.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Top with cheese and potato chip mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together. Add remaining ingredients. Make into rolls; wrap in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator. Remove and slice thin. Bake on cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken mushroom bake
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour.
Melt butter in shallow baking dish.
Arrange chicken in a single layer, skin side down. (Remove skin if you prefer.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn skin side down; combine mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over and continue to bake 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: garlic bubble bread
directions: Allow bread to thaw, then cut in 10 to 12 slices to speed final thawing.
Mix together margarine, egg, garlic salt and parsley flakes.
Cut bread in walnut-size pieces.
Dunk each piece in margarine mix.
Place in Bundt pan or bread loaf pan or muffin tins.
Allow to rise.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spicy pasta pie
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package.
Drain well; set aside. Meanwhile in a large skillet, cook turkey sausage, onion and garlic until sausage is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, Italian seasoning and crushed pepper.
Spray a casserole dish with nonstick coating.
Place half of the cooked vermicelli in the bottom of the dish.
Top with half of the sausage mixture and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover the dish loosely with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: american goulash
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Add corn and macaroni to beef mixture.
Add just a little over half a can of tomato paste.
Add barbecue sauce and water.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cool until thick.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Mix together. Refrigerate. Cut into squares. (Top with cherry.)

title: johnny cake
directions: Stir sugar, egg and lard well.
Add milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: party mix
directions: Mix melted margarine, bacon fat, celery and garlic salts and Worcestershire sauce together. Pour over cereals and pretzels and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Add nuts and bake another hour. Stir about every 20 to 30 minutes.
Use a large roasting pan.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Place on a plate covered with paper towels and pat out excess grease.
Remove all but about 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Fry onions in drippings until golden and allow to cool in skillet.
Blend in flour, sugar and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until bubbly.
Remove from heat and add water and vinegar.
Return to stove and stir until mixture thickens.
Pour warm sauce over sliced potatoes. Crumble bacon and sprinkle over all.
Lightly mix through.

title: lasagne
directions: In pan, brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic, pepper and oregano.
Simmer uncovered about 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in pan.
Spread 1 cup sauce, then alternate layers of lasagne, sauce and cheese, ending sauce and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices in large bowl.
Add eggs, evaporated milk and milk; mix well.
Pour mixture into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes, until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: raggedy ann cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, shortening, egg and mapleine.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix in coconut.
Drop onto pan; dip bottom of greased glass into sugar and press cookie flat.
Bake 10-12 minutes at 350°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Spread each layer evenly in a large (4-quart) dish:

title: spinach stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Combine all the ingredients except chicken.
Mix well.
Divide mixture into eighths.
At neck end of each piece of chicken, carefully lift skin.
With long handled spoon, fill space between skin and meat with one-eighth spinach mixture, taking care not to break membrane connecting skin to meat.
Tuck ends of chicken under, and place in ovenproof baking dish.
Repeat process with remaining chicken.
Bake, covered, in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 30 minutes.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: kathryn's liver and onion gravy
directions: Salt, pepper and flour liver. Brown in oil on both sides.
Set aside.
Cook sliced onion in same oil. Set aside.

Brown the self-rising flour in the same oil. Add hot water, one cup at a time, until desired consistency. Return liver and onion to gravy. Cook about 20 minutes. Add more water and seasoning as needed.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Add walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour (may vary depending on size of loaf pans).
Makes 3 small loaves or 2 large loaves.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Then, mix in order and cook over medium heat in Dutch oven or deep iron skillet.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together with electric mixer.
Spread in casserole dish.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with about 1/2 cup milk.
Combine with sugar, flour and remaining milk.
Cook until thick (approximately 5 minutes).
Add vanilla, coconut and margarine; mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Combine Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla and beat mixture well.
Pour over cake.
Make sure mixture goes through all of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
When serving, use cherries or strawberries.

title: mina's mango cobbler
directions: Spray 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam. Line bottom of pan with mango chunks. Mix cornstarch and lime juice; pour over fruit. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit. Dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken rice caribe
directions: Brown chicken parts and pour off oil.
Add water, garlic, oregano and salt to chicken, cover and cook slowly 15 minutes. Add soup, green pepper and rice.
Cook 30 more minutes covered, or until liquid is absorbed (stir a bit).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in flour, soda and oatmeal. Press small amount of dough between hands.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Cook a medium size cauliflower (whole) 12 to 15 minutes. Drain well.
Place it on a baking plate.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard and spread on cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add water.
Boil until a few drops of syrup harden as soon as dropped in a little ice water.
Remove from fire and add nuts.
Stir fast until mixture begins to sugar. Try to coat all nuts evenly.
Pour out on waxed paper and break apart.
Discard cinnamon stick.

title: potato-corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add corn liquid with just enough mix to make moderately thick dough.
Shape into patties.
Dredge in additional flour.
Fry until crisp and golden.
Makes 4 to 6 fritters.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, 2 1/2 cups flour, shortening, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix with spoon until well blended, then beat with a spoon about four minutes.
Add remaining flour (dough should be soft and sticky).
Turn
out and knead about three minutes. Shape dough into a loaf and place in a greased pan.
Let it rise about one hour until double.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes one loaf.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine confectioners sugar, cream cheese and eggs. Mix well and pour over other mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Drop into muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: strawberry angel
directions: Slice cake into 3 layers.
Blend remaining ingredients, spoon between layers on top and sides.
Chill.

title: yum yum pie
directions: Line pan with cinnamon crackers.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and a little over half of the Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spread over cracker layer.
Pour pie filling for next layer, then a layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Top evenly with coconut, then sweetened condensed milk.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
In small saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with peanut butter.
Spread evenly over hot coconut layer.
Cool 30 minutes.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into bars.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar and oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to zucchini, mix.
Stir well, add nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Recipe works best with 1 (9 x 5-inch) and 1 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack. Freezes well.

title: allie's pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Peel onions and put both in food chopper and grind.
Put in kettle.
Cover with boiling water; let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Again cover with boiling water.
Bring to boiling point and let stand 10 minutes; drain as dry as possible.
Return to kettle and add vinegar and sugar.
Bring to boiling point; let simmer 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Add vegetables to chicken stock.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In a saucepan, melt butter; add flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Add half and half; cook until thick.
Mix with vegetables and cheese.

title: blackberry cobbler(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine and set aside.
Combine flour and baking powder in a small bowl.
Add 1/2 cup apple juice concentrate, 1/4 cup fructose and water.
Mix well.
Pour batter over melted butter.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Make crust of pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Make filling of cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Stir in whipped topping.
Spread on crust.
Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in strawberries.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and chill.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Preheat oil. Combine 1/2 cup oil and egg; beat well. Add rest of ingredients and stir until well blended. Coat shrimp with batter. Fry for 60 seconds or until golden brown.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Combine sugar, salad dressing, flour and baking soda.
Cut up dates with soda and pour hot water over them.
Add to first ingredients.
Add nutmeats.
Pour into a greased and floured square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve plain or with Dream Whip.
Very moist.

title: chili dip
directions: In 8 x 8-inch pan, spread cream cheese. Spoon chili over cream cheese. Cover with lots of Velveeta cheese. Heat (microwave) until cheese melts. Serve with corn chips.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix at high speed the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add pineapple and bread crumbs.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes, or until lightly browned, at 350°.

title: lemon bread
directions: Blend margarine, 2 cups of sugar and eggs.
Sift next 3 ingredients together, add alternately to cream mixture with buttermilk.
fold in lemon rind and pecans.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Mix remaining sugar and lemon juice.
Spoon over hot bread.
Cool 1 hour before serving.

title: no-knead rolls
directions: Blend together milk, 3 tablespoons shortening, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm by adding water.
Add yeast and mix well.
Add egg.
Add flour gradually, mixing until dough is well blended. Place in greased bowl.
Brush top with melted shortening and allow to rise until light.
Knead dough a few times to make smooth ball. Form into desired shapes and bake in 400° oven for 15 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: ground beef dip(serves 8)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce, ketchup and oregano; cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Spoon off excess fat.
Remove from heat.
Add cheeses; stir until melted.
Serve warm with king size corn chips.

title: all-season's punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in the water. Mix in the Kool-Aid and pineapple. Add ginger ale before serving. Serves 50 punch cup servings.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine
cucumbers,
onions,
celery,
hot
peppers and ground peppers
and
add salt and water.
Let stand overnight, then drain.
Next
mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed. Heat
mixture
to
boiling	and add drained vegetables. Cook slowly 10 minutes.	Place in jars and seal.

title: kale soup
directions: Add water to ham soup bone to make 2-quarts of stock or more. Cook vegetables until done, then add kale and a little parsley. You can add cabbage also if you like.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Fry sweet potatoes in hot oil in skillet until brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Add milk.
Simmer on low heat until tender.
Serve hot.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Put sugar and enough water to dissolve sugar into a gallon container.
Add the rest of ingredients and stir well.
Add enough water to fill container.
Add red food coloring to make it pretty.

title: easy trail mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pack 1/2 cup portions in small plastic bags.
Store in airtight container in cool, dry place.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Place shredded potatoes and onion in a medium mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk and melted butter and blend.
Then add flour, salt and pepper and mix.
Place 1/4 cup scoops of mixture onto a hot, greased griddle.
Spread to make a 4-inch pancake.
Brown on each side.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Soften cream cheese at Medium-high power for about 2 minutes. Add butter and half and half. Microwave for another 45 to 60 seconds at Medium-high to High power until butter is melted. Stir at least once. Add frosting mix. Microwave at High power for about 2 minutes, stirring and whisking until mixture is smooth and creamy. Let stand 2 minutes. Add peppermint extract and food coloring of your choice. Roll mixture into balls or drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper dusted with powdered sugar, if desired. Press with fork for decorated top, if desired. Let mint stand at room temperature for about 4 hours.

title: grilled chicken taco
directions: In skillet, heat oil.
Cook onion and garlic until tender. Add chicken.
Heat 3 minutes.
Remove from pan into bowl.
Heat tortillas according to package. Divide chicken onto center of tortillas.
Top with cheese and optional ingredients. Fold tortillas in half.
Melt margarine in same skillet.
Grill tacos on each side for 2 or 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 8 to 10 tacos.

title: ground meat soup
directions: Mix (as in meat loaf) meat, vegetables, eggs, cheese and parsley together in a large pot.
Slowly run cold water down the side of the pan so as not to disturb meat mixture and cover meat with water.
Heat pot to slow boil and start to break up meat mixture with large spoon in bit size pieces.
Add pizza sauce, canned beans (juice and all), spinach (chopped and drained) and season to taste.
Cook for 1 hour or when vegetables are tender. Add cooked pasta of your choice (large or small shells are nice).

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix hash browns with melted cheese, mayo and onion.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Fold in sour cream.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and pecans together and place in bottom of Bundt pan (greased).
Add 1/2 batter, add remainder of sugar mixture, then balance of batter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: date dessert
directions: Cut dates and nutmeats.
Add to well beaten eggs and sugar. Add flour and baking powder.
Bake in a shallow greased pan (8 x 8-inch) for about 25 minutes at 325° to 350°; cool.
When done, break into pieces
and serve mixed with Cool Whip.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Add bread crumbs and cheese, cut up rather fine.
Add salt and egg yolks, beaten to lemon color.
Cook while beating egg whites stiff.
Fold in egg whites and bake 20 minutes.

title: bonnie's walnut surprise
directions: Put in pan and put nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: triple orange salad
directions: Pour boiling water on jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add orange sherbet.
Stir until melted.
Stir in 1 can oranges.
Pour into an 8-inch square glass pan.
Mix remaining orange segments, pineapple, coconut and marshmallows.
Fold in sour cream. Refrigerate at least 3 hours, then spread on top of jello.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill 10-inch pie plate with sliced apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar on apples.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, salt, melted butter, 1 egg and walnuts in a bowl.
Mix well and then pour over apples in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crabmeat blend casserole
directions: Saute crabmeat blend with onion and butter.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Allow to cool and serve cold or put into casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
This can be served hot as a casserole or cold with crackers.

title: fresh fried corn
directions: Cut corn from each ear by first splitting each row down the center.
Then cut from cob.
Scrape cob for the extra milk.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute meat lightly. Add chili powder, corn, tomato sauce and water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Pour into 2-inch deep baking dish. Spread corn meal topping over all and bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: jalapeno hot corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, whip eggs and milk together. Add all liquid ingredients. Add meal, to which baking powder, salt and sugar have been added. Mix well. Stir in grated cheese. Pour into oiled pan. Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes. This bread freezes well. Cut into squares and wrap in foil to freeze.

title: microwave tuna wedges
directions: In large glass bowl, beat eggs with a fork.
Add rice, onions and undrained tuna, mixing well.
Melt butter in microwave, about 1 minute on High.
Add to tuna along with thyme and crumbs, mixing well.
Evenly spread mixture in lightly greased 9-inch glass pie plate.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High about 9 to 11 minutes, rotating dish halfway after 5 minutes.
Garnish with cheese and tomato wedges.
This is great on a hot summer when you have fresh garden tomatoes.

title: meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water. Add boiling water and cook until clear and thick. Chill. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Turn to low speed. Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until dissolved. Add salt and vanilla. Beat in cold cornstarch mixture, then at high speed, beat well. Spread on pie. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Beat well.
Add zucchini.
Beat well.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup, bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Spread into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Melt chips together and spread over top of cereal mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix milk into softened cream cheese; add mayo and horseradish and mix well.
Add onions, tuna, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce and mix well.
Sprinkle with paprika and chill for 1 hour.

title: onion-tuna quiche
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer or until top is browned.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk sherbet
directions: Thoroughly mix buttermilk, sugar and pineapple.
Pour into ice cube tray and freeze to a mush.
Pour mixture into a large bowl and beat until smooth.
Blend in the beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Return to refrigerator tray.
An increase in volume now will require two trays.
Freeze until firm.

title: lazy day pie
directions: Mix in bowl first five ingredients.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan, pour dough
into
butter, then put desired amount of fruit (any kind) over top
of
dough.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ice cream.
Let chill. Before serving, you can stir in ice cream if desired.

title: caramel corn
directions: Remove all unpopped kernels.
Put popcorn into a 17 x 2 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a saucepan combine sugar, butter or margarine and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat until butter melts and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook without stirring for 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla. Pour over popcorn.
Stir to coat popcorn.
Bake for 15 minutes; stir and bake 5 to 10 minutes more.
Pour corn into a large bowl; cool.
Makes 8 cups.

title: top of stove meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix beef, crumbs, 1/4 cup soup, onion, egg and seasoning.
Shape firmly into 2 loaves.
Brown on both sides in skillet in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Cover and cook on low heat for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Pour remaining soup, mixed with water and mustard, over loaves.
Top with cheese and cook.

title: munner's cracklin corn bread
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour in greased iron frying pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: polish sauerkraut
directions: Wash and drain sauerkraut.
Add shredded cabbage, onion, apple, salt, pepper, sugar and water.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour in a covered casserole.
Fry salt pork while sauerkraut is cooking.
Add 2 tablespoons flour and brown slowly.
Add pork to sauerkraut and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot nectar.
Dissolve plain gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix together.
Add enough cold water to make 3 1/2 cups.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add grated cream cheese, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Stir together cornstarch, ginger, broth and soy sauce until smooth; set aside.

title: mexican squash
directions: Cook squash with just enough water to prevent sticking.

When tender, mash squash. Add onion, butter, salt, pepper and sage. Cook over low heat uncovered until liquid is gone. Cool to lukewarm. Fold in cheese and cracker crumbs, chilies and milk. Pour into buttered baking dish and top with some additional cheese and cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pioneer meat
directions: Brown the beef and strain the fat off.
Add all ingredients, mix well and cook on medium heat, first 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot hamburger dish
directions: Brown beef and onions until done.
Drain meat.
Combine remaining ingredients, except biscuits, and add to beef.
Pour in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with biscuits and bake until biscuits are done.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt together; add eggs and mix well. Add margarine, vanilla and milk; mix well.
Add coconut and pecans, mix.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon to crisp.
Crumble and drain. Brown meat, cook onions, add rest of ingredients and stir well. Put in 3 1/2-quart dish.
Cooks about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together. Roll into balls. Put in refrigerator.

title: walnut chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix gently until well coated. Refrigerate.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or wrapped in flour tortillas.

title: cakey brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and chocolate.
Stir and remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt; stir.
Add eggs and mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Wash spinach and trim off stems.
In a large pot, steam spinach 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain and squeeze out water, then chop.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter and saute onion, mushrooms and garlic until onion is translucent.
Stir in flour and remove from heat. Gradually stir in milk, oregano, salt, basil and pepper.
Return to heat, stir constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir a little hot mixture into eggs, return egg mixture to sauce and cook 1 minute, stirring.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Spread a thin layer of sauce in a 9 x 13-inch shallow pan.
Layer half the noodles in the dish; spread chopped spinach over noodles.
Spoon half the sauce over the spinach.
Cover with half the tomato slices, all the Ricotta cheese and half the sliced Mozzarella.
Layer remaining noodles, tomatoes and sauce.
Top with Mozzarella.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes until hot and fluffy.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: mama's bread pudding
directions: Warm milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Do not boil.
Break toast in small pieces.
Pour milk mixture over toast pieces.
Put in 9 x 11-inch buttered pan or ovenproof dish.
Let bread soak 10 minutes or more.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top of pudding. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Sift all dry ingredients together and gradually add to sugar mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well all ingredients.
Place in a cold oven and bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: oven pot roast with beer(servings: 8.  preparation time:  3 hours.)
directions: *Use chuck roast or similar cut.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Alternately add buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Mix hot water and cocoa and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool.

title: steak sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and cook in saucepan; simmer for 5 minutes, then put in old clean sauce bottle.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Salt and pepper hash browns and put aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered and then for 20 minutes uncovered.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Saut steak in oil until brown. Add onions and cook 2 minutes. Stir in carrots, wine, broth, mushrooms with liquid and seasonings. (Boil water for rice.) Bring steak mixture to a boil (start rice). Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Add celery and cook 10 minutes longer. Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water. Stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: smoky sausage chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in saucepan; drain.
Sprinkle chili powder and cumin over meat; cook and stir 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients except optional toppings; bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Stir.
Ladle into bowls; top as desired and serve with additional picante sauce. Serves 6.

title: corn chowder
directions: Place potatoes, peppers and onion in water in 5-quart casserole with tightly fitting lid.
Cook, covered, at 100% power in high power oven, 12 minutes or 24 minutes in a low power oven.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken; debone and break into small pieces.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush tortilla chips.
Layer half of the ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish in the following order: tortilla chips, chicken, soup, enchilada sauce, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch surprise
directions: Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Spread mixture over cooled crust.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Put on top of cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cover and cool.

title: presbyterian chicken
directions: Spread rice on bottom of casserole.
Put chicken on rice, skin side up. Dilute mushroom soup with milk or water and pour over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until rice is cooked.

title: peanut butter banana pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, combine milk and pudding mixes until blended.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat; stir in 1/2 c. peanut butter until blended. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs; beat alternately with dry ingredients.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Bake in any pan.

title: round steak with sour cream gravy
directions: Brown steak with onion in butter.
Add water, salt and paprika.
Cover tightly and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Check periodically that the water hasn't boiled out.
Add sour cream and mushrooms and thicken to your liking with cornstarch.
Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.
Serves 4.

title: ice cream pudding pie
directions: Thoroughly blend milk and ice cream in a bowl.
Add pie filling; mix.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or at low speed of electric mixer until blended, about 1 minute.
Pour immediately into pie crust.
Chill until set, about 3 hours.
Garnish with prepared or thawed frozen whipped topping, if desired.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with one stick margarine and spread in large Pyrex dish.
Beat eggs, remaining margarine and powdered sugar.
(Beat with mixer for 15 minutes or until light and fluffy.)
Spread mixture on cracker crumbs.
Add sliced bananas and spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Top with cherries and pecans.

title: lemon daffodil
directions: Mix lemon juice with Eagle Brand milk and sugar.
Fold in Cool whip.
Add angel food cake and mix well.
Garnish with grated lemon or lemon slices. Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Bake in a 350° oven in a loaf pan, which has been greased and floured, for 40 minutes or until tests done with toothpick inserted into cake.

title: simply tasty cheese sauce
directions: Mix sour cream and cheese together and heat in microwave stirring every 30 seconds until warmed and cheese is melted. Do not boil.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and butter until crumbly.
Arrange apples in bottom of unbaked pastry shell. Sprinkle the crumbly mixture over apples.
Spoon sour cream over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: tropical carrot cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Prepare carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs lightly; beat in sugar.
Stir in oil, dry ingredients, carrots and pineapple (you should have 3/4 cup pineapple); mix well.
Stir in walnuts and coconut.
Spread evenly in pans.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until sides shrink slightly and top springs back when touched.
Cool layers in pans for 10 minutes, then turn out onto wire racks to cool completely.
Frost with a cream cheese icing or white frosting.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Beat together peanut butter and 1/4 cup margarine.
Stir in 10x sugar.
Stir in cereal.
Using one tablespoon of dough, shape into logs.
Roll in nuts; set aside.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add kidney beans, taco seasoning and 1 to 1 1/2 cups of water.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: the orchard inn's tomato herb soup
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add flour, stirring constantly.
Cook lightly and slowly. Add milk, then chicken stock. Add parsley and basil.
In a
large stockpot, blend roux with tomatoes and tomato juice.
Heat to boiling and add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve piping hot with garnish of Parmesan cheese. Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Layer squash, meat, onion and rice in casserole dish.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grandma's homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour and salt and add to scalded milk. Cook until thickened.
Cool and add vanilla.
Put in freezer and add enough milk and some half and half until freezer is 2/3 full. This is for a gallon freezer.

title: "yummy" white bread
directions: Place ingredients in order listed into bread machine.
Set machine on white bread.
When completed, enjoy your no-fat bread!

title: granola cereal(don't overcook)
directions: Mix together rolled oats and 2 cups of any of the combinations listed.
Combine separately the liquids, peanut butter, milk or cream.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Bake in large pans 30 to 60 minutes in 300° oven, stirring every 10 minutes.
When cool, if desired, add any of the following:
raisins, chopped dates, dried apples or apricots.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in all but 1/3 cup onions.
Spoon mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Heat orange juice.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Beat in orange sherbet until well blended.
Add orange slices; mix until well coated.
Pour into mold.
Chill 2 hours until set.
Double the recipe to fill a Bundt pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Squeeze out excess juice.
Mix and bake at 400°
for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add Accent to cream cheese.
Chop ingredients.
Add to cream cheese.
Mix.
Form into ball.
Sprinkle with paprika to garnish.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from beans and peas.
Cut pimentos, onion, celery and pepper into small pieces.
Pour oil, sugar, vinegar and salt over vegetables in container.
Place cover on container and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, drain off liquid. Will keep for days.

title: baked spiced fruit
directions: Drain the first 4 ingredients, reserving 2 cups mixed juice. Arrange fruit in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.
combine juice and remaining ingredients, except pecans in a small saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until slightly thickened. Pour sauce over fruit and top with pecans.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: grandma bessie's brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo or butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and baking soda 3 times.
Add flour mixture.
Roll in wax paper and chill.
Slice.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: soft lemon cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, salt and food coloring; blend thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll out small portions of dough at a time; cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet; if desired, sprinkle with sugar over top of cookies. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 24 servings.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo; add chicken, rice, vegetables and soy sauce.
Mix soup, broth and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Add to first mixture and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cashews. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with chow mein noodles before serving.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Place cabbage and onions in layers in a large bowl.
Pour 3/4 cup sugar over this mixture.
Bring vinegar, salt, 1 teaspoon sugar, mustard seed and prepared mustard to a boil.
Add vegetable oil.
Beat mixture well.
Spoon over cabbage mixture.
Cover and let set in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks.

title: roast beef and yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix together flour and 1 cup milk.
Add eggs one at a time, stirring after each.
Add rest of the milk.
Grease long cake pan with roast beef juice or Crisco.
Heat in 400° oven slightly then add batter.
Bake in hot oven for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately with roast beef.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not overbake! While warm, place onto serving plate, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: coconut rum balls
directions: Combine crumbs, coconut and nuts in a bowl.
Stir in condensed milk and rum, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in confectioners sugar to coat.
Cover and store in refrigerator. Roll again in sugar just before serving.
Makes 6 dozen candies.

title: mozzarella 'n beef casserole
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Roll in crushed Rice Krispies and cornflakes.
Melt margarine and dribble over coated chicken pieces.
Place chicken on cookie sheet and cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes and uncover. Continue baking for another 30 minutes or until chicken is golden brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet and saute garlic, onion and rice until garlic and onion are soft.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, until the water has evaporated.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: corn(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cook bacon strips until crisp. Drain.
To part of bacon drippings, add rest of ingredients.
Cook over low heat, covered, for 5 to 8 minutes.
Top with bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until cake tests done. Cool cake in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely.

title: linda's cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until almost done.
Cool and peel.
Grate and add sour cream, pepper, salt, green onions and butter.
Mix, then add 1/2 of the cheese.
Mix and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt chocolate and add to scalded milk.
Mix together cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add chocolate and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Pour into ice cube tray and freeze until mushy consistency.
Whip the cream.
Add vanilla, then fold into chocolate mixture.
Return to ice tray, wet bottom and freeze.

title: baked ham
directions: Trim the outside of ham, then rub ham

with brown sugar and bake 16 or 17 minutes per pound at 300 or 325°. When done remove from oven, pour vinegar over ham and return to oven for 15 minutes. Mix corn starch, pineapple topping, sugar and mustard. Cook and stir over medium heat until dissolved. Baste ham and return to oven
for 15 minutes.

title: coconut-orange tartlets
directions: Measure flour, sugar and salt into bowl.
Cut in butter thoroughly.
Beat egg slightly; pour into flour mixture.
Mix until flour is moistened.
Gather into a ball.
Wrap.
Chill 4 hours or until firm.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except salad oil; mix well.
Drop mixture by tablespoons into 1/8 inch hot oil in large skillet. Flatten patties to 1/4 inch thick.
Cook until golden brown, turn and brown on other side.
Yield:
About 14.

title: best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt chocolate and oleo together on top of stove; stir occasionally. Dump mixture into large bowl.
Add sugar; blend well.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Dump into greased pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out almost clean.
Makes 24 brownies.
Frost with Simple Chocolate Frosting.

title: cheddar-pecan cheese ball
directions: Bring Cheddar cheese and cream cheese to room temperature. In medium mixing bowl, beat cheeses, sour cream, mustard and onion powder with an electric mixer on medium speed until well combined. Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Shape into a ball.
Coat ball with chopped pecans.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 1 ball (about 2 1/3 cups.).

title: veggie burger patties
directions: Dried herbs can be substituted, use smaller amounts.

title: hot rolls
directions: Boil 1 cup water and 3/4 cup shortening until the shortening melts.
In mixing bowl, add 1 1/2 cups water, sugar and salt; mix. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Beat egg and add to water mixture; mix well.
Sift 4 cups flour and add to the mixture. Measure 4 1/2 cups more flour and add enough to make a soft dough. Put in greased bowl; cover and let rise 2 to 3 times.
Make rolls and place in greased pan.
Let rise again; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl, add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Spread frosting between layers, all sides and top, sprinkle top with 1 cup pecans.

title: microwave white squash
directions: Select small white squashes no more than 4-inches across.
Cut into halves at the scalloped edge.
Place halves into shallow baking pie plate with small amount of water.
Microwave High power until tender or can be easily pricked with a toothpick.

title: applenutter treats
directions: Mix peanut butter and cornflakes in a bowl.
Spread on apple slices or half apples.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruits.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter, add brown sugar and curry; spoon over fruit.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: tuna and cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain tuna.
Flake.
Combine with cheese, seasonings, carrot, chives and olives.
Add small amount French dressing or mayonnaise if desired.
Chill thoroughly.
Heap into cabbage or lettuce leaf. Makes 6 servings.

title: elena's italian filled cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture. Make a soft dough.
Make balls the size of walnuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix in order and pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Delicious.

title: chicken amandine
directions: In skillet, melt 1 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Add almonds and cook until brown.
Remove and set aside.
In flat dish, combine all seasonings.
Coat chicken in flour; pour over seasonings.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix the sour cream and the taco mix.
Put the ingredients in dish in layers in the order listed.
Garnish top with green onions and black olives.

title: quick salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer. Chill 1 hour. Serve with taco chips.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar; beat until thickest.
Add rum and cream.
Add ice cream; do not mix.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Mix melted ice cream.

title: pecan carrot cake
directions: Measure and sift together all dry ingredients.
Blend in vegetable oil and eggs.
Fold in grated carrots and chopped pecans. Pour in 2 cake pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 360° oven.
Ice with simple confectioners sugar icing.

title: special kugel
directions: Boil noodles.
Put in greased dish.
Add egg yolks, sugar, fruit cocktail, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat egg whites and add. Mix thoroughly.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets. Combine flour, butter, salt and milk for sauce on stove. Add grated cheese to hot sauce.
Stir until dissolved. Pour over potatoes that are cooked, peeled and diced.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 2 minutes on each side; do not cook longer.
Add chives, lime juice, brandy, parsley and mustard to pan; cook for 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Add rest of oil and butter.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and cut carrots into bite-size pieces.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar and tomato soup together in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over warm carrots.
Add green pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: garlic baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; cut into cubes with skin on, about 1 inch square.
Put in bowl.
Add oil and mix to coat.
Mix garlic, parsley, pepper and salt in a bag; shake.
Add potatoes to bag and shake to coat.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: curried pork chops
directions: Trim fat from meat.
If desired, sprinkle with salt and pepper. In a large skillet cook chops in margarine.
Cook for 5-7 minutes. Remove chops.
Add apple to drippings and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in parsley, flour, curry and bouillon.
Add milk or cream all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in wine or water.
Return chops to skillet covering both sides with sauce. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
To serve, spoon sauce and apples over chops.
Serves:

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Cook ingredients over medium heat until liquid cooks out.
Put on buttered cookie sheet and cook for 15 minutes at 350°.
Add a dash of salt, stir and cook 15 additional minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add cracker crumbs and dill seed; saute until brown.
Slice cabbage coarsely.
Boil until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
(Do not overcook.)
Place cabbage in 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil. Add onion, garlic, bacon and green pepper.
Saute until golden brown. Add beef and stir until lightly brown. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and bring to a quick boil.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add beans and simmer an additional 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Add to taco sauce mix and 3/4 cup water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Transfer to large bowl and cool.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix water and margarine in 12 x 8-inch baking dish until margarine is melted.
Stir in stuffing mix and 1/4 cup of the salsa.
Arrange chicken over stuffing.
Pour remaining 1/2 cup salsa over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frosted salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add carbonated beverage, chill until partially set.
Drain pineapple, saving juice for topping.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Pour into spring-form or other pan.
Chill until set. Add topping and chill overnight.

title: fried cheese sticks
directions: Cut cheese slices into halves; roll until cheese forms sticks. Coat with flour.
Dip in egg.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil in skillet for 1 minute.
Turn.
Fry for 1 minute longer or until golden brown.
Drain well.
Arrange on serving dish.
Makes 16 servings.

title: oriental chicken and noodles
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Heat oil in a deep skillet or wok and saute chicken in heated oil for 5 minutes.
Add cabbage, celery and sprouts.
Mix well; cover and cook over low heat for 3 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions, then add to chicken mixture.
In separate bowl, combine cornstarch and broth and stir into chicken mixture until sauce has thickened. Sprinkle with scallions, caraway seeds and lemon juice, and serve.

title: lots of biscuits
directions: Cut lard into flour until it resembles meal.
(Use a large bowl.)
Make a hole in the center of flour and pour in all the buttermilk.
Mix well until all the flour in bowl is well mixed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, cut into small pieces.
Boil noodles according to directions on package; drain.
Add soup, drained vegetables, chicken and 1 cup cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 50 - 55 minutes.

title: southwest chili
directions: In stew pot saute beef, onion, green pepper and garlic for 10 to 15 minutes.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, about 30 minutes.
Serve with cheese and onions.
Serves up to 10 people.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Dot butter over top. Bake in pan of hot water.
Bake at 300° for about 3 1/2 hours or until firm and light brown on top.

title: stew
directions: Brown stew meat.
Blend golden mushroom soup, tomato paste and 4 cups of water.
Add stew meat; let cook on low heat until meat is tender.
Add stew seasoning.
Let cook 15 minutes.
Let's eat!

title: elegant crab appetizer
directions: Pick crab to remove any pieces of shell.
Combine the ketchup, horseradish and lemon juice.
Set aside.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
