Soften cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Add to jello.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and pecan pieces.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: chicken divan
directions: In casserole dish with no stick spray, layer broccoli followed by chicken.

title: ham balls in zesty sauce
directions: Combine meats, milk, eggs and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Form into small balls and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Makes about 30 or 15 loaves.

title: hamburger, potatoes and beans(1944 war time recipe - woman's day)
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Add just enough water to cover. Cook until tender.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% Bran and set aside.
Cream together the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk, All-Bran, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add raisins. Fold Bran mixture in very carefully.
Do not stir.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Batter will keep in the refrigerator for a month or more and bake as needed.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and orange juice as directed.
Add pineapple and orange juice.
Make the day before it is to be used so the juices will blend.
Refrigerate.
Serves 100 punch cup servings.
When serving, put ice ring in punch bowl.
Pour punch over it.
You may use any flavor of Kool-Aid.

title: peanut butter log(peanut butter play dough)
directions: Knead milk into peanut butter.
Mix all together.
Roll in coconut or wheat germ.
Enjoy, play and eat.

title: puerto rican arroz con gandules(rice with pigeon peas)
directions: In a large saucepan or rice pot, heat oil.
When oil is hot, saute onions, then add peppers, reco leaves and chorizo. Saute until chorizo is brown.
Add olives, garlic, sofrito, sazon and tomato sauce.
Add rinsed rice and water. Add black pepper, oregano and adobo.

title: mexi meat pie
directions: Fry until brown:
ground chuck, onions and green pepper. Drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Need corn and Cheddar cheese. Can also use sliced black or green olives, if you like.
Place bottom crust in deep 11-inch pie dish.
Top with 1/3 of cheese. Add meat and sauce mixture.
Top with corn, then the rest of the cheese, then the sliced olives if you wish.
Top with crust.
Cut steam vents in crust.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes, then cut and serve.

title: connie r's chili
directions: Brown ground beef in 5-quart Dutch oven. Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread half of the bread cubes in dish.
Cut cream cheese into small cubes and sprinkle half over bread in pan.
Repeat, layering with remaining bread and cream cheese.
Whisk eggs, milk and maple syrup in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with additional maple syrup.
Makes 10 servings.
Great for family or friends get together served with bacon or sausage.

title: the best pecan pie in the world
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and butter over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Slowly blend hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Add pecans, vanilla and salt.
Blend.
Bake in unbaked pie shell 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage; add seasonings.
Put into pan and cook until about half done.
Add tomatoes.
Mix together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with a topping of Pepperidge Farm dressing. Top with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cover lettuce with layer of onion, cauliflower and bacon. Place Miracle Whip on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and sugar. Cover and place in the refrigerator overnight.
Toss salad 30 minutes before serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Simmer for about 15 minutes and serve on buns.

title: charlie's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: serbian cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in shallow 4-quart casserole.
Pour in milk; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scallop casserole(serves 6)
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except scallops.
Pour over scallops.

title: greek wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine until creamy.
Add sugar, egg and extract, beating well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Roll small pieces of dough into small crescent shapes with hands.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until golden, about 12 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar over the cookies while still hot.
Cool and store airtight.
Makes about 40.

title: sweet potato pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Peel potatoes; slice fairly thin, cover with water and cook until tender.
Measure (press fairly firm) and place in a large mixing bowl.
On low speed, whip well (clean beaters).
Add butter while potatoes are warm, then add sugar, egg, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add coconut and stir in well.
Pour into unbaked (deep dish) pie shell.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) until filling is set and begins to brown.
(Oven temperatures may vary.)

title: pecan coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and shortening together as you would pie crust.
Take out 1/2 cup mixture; save for topping.
To the remainder, add the buttermilk and teaspoon of soda which has been dissolved in a tablespoon of warm water, vanilla, salt and egg. Beat together.
Turn into buttered pan approximately 9 1/2 inches square.
Sprinkle over top the 1/2 cup of crumbs and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Best served slightly warm.
(Serves 12.)

title: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add vanilla, food coloring and eggs; mix well.
Add flour and cocoa, alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in soda dissolved in vinegar.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes in two 8-inch or 9-inch round cake pans, greased and floured.

title: green onion dip
directions: Blend all ingredients; cover and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pizza bread
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Mix mayonnaise and soft butter together, add remaining ingredients and spread on sliced bread.
Bake 350° for 10-15 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt. Add vanilla and nuts.
Roll in small balls; pat out and cook at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Do not grease pan.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: e z veggie bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions.
Let cool after cooking.
In a large bowl, mix Cheddar cheese, egg whites, onions, mushroom soup, mayonnaise and vegetables.

title: seafood salad
directions: Grind in food chopper the tuna, crabmeat, eggs, pickles, celery and onion.
Blend vinegar, mayonnaise, sugar, seasoning salt and cream cheese together.
Combine all ingredients and chill well.
Garnish with stuffed olives.
Grinding all ingredients makes a smooth salad.
Wonderful for sandwiches, also.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs
until
fluffy.
Add
the other ingredients. Blend nuts in
last.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind cured ham and fresh pork together.
Beat eggs and add with milk to ground meat.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pat into loaf.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Cook meat; drain well.
Add all ingredients.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti.
Parmesan cheese can be offered for topping.

title: salad in the pink
directions: Drain pineapple well; reserve all juice.
Add juice to Jell-O in a saucepan and stir in 1 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly until gelatin is dissolved.
Reduce heat and stir in cranberry sauce.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice, peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Blend in sour cream, then fold in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold or 13 x 9-inch pan; chill until firm.
Serve on salad greens.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain and add 1 stick oleo and milk.
Whip.
Add sour cream, onion, chives and cheese.
Mix.
Pour into Pam coated pan or dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: chocolate-topped custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in hot milk; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 425° until knife inserted just off center comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Cool. Melt chocolate with 4 teaspoons milk over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in additional milk, a few drops of a time, until of spreading consistency.
Quickly spread over the pie.
Chill.

title: christmas casserole
directions: Beat eggs and sugar gradually until fluffy.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Place in greased casserole (2-quart).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and stir with wooden spoon.
When cool, roll into balls in powdered sugar.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place Rice Krispies crumbs, black pepper, salt and paprika in a plastic freezer bag, shaking to mix thoroughly.
Brush thawed chicken with margarine and place in freezer bag, shaking until chicken is coated with cereal mixture. Place in oven and cook for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Put brisket in large cooking bag.
Add full bottle of barbecue sauce.
Place in roaster.
Cook 3 to 4 hours at 325°.
Very tender and very economical.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Beat spices, sugar, salt, eggs and oil together.
Add baking powder into flour.
Add nuts.
Stir well.
Put into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chess bars
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients well and spread in a 9 x 13 pan. Then beat rest of ingredients. Pour over the other mixture and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon granola
directions: In large bowl, combine oats, coconut, pecans, sesame seed, oil, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in honey, oil and vanilla; mix thoroughly. Divide mixture into 2 equal parts.
Bake half of oats mixture in a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pans in preheated 325° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 1/2 fruit. Cool.
Stir with a fork until crumbly.
Repeat for remaining 1/2 oats mixture.
Serve with cold milk.
Store in a tightly covered container in the refrigerator.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: grilled jalapeno chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thick.
Combine lime juice and next 2 ingredients; add chicken and marinate at least 1 hour. Grill or broil chicken until done, approximately 7 minutes per side, basting occasionally with marinade.

title: dirt pie(kids recipe)
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix.
Beat until well blended, 1 or 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir 1 cup cookies and the chips or peanuts into pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm. Garnish with gumdrop flowers, if desired.

title: steak with horseradish sauce
directions: Using a sharp knife, score the surface of the steak with shallow diagonal cuts at 1-inch intervals, making diamond shapes. Repeat on the other side.
In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the next five ingredients.
Add steak.
Seal bag and turn to coat.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Mix by hand.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Make a well in center.
Add margarine and combine pumpkin, egg and water.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: dump cake(great for kids to make)
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour crushed pineapple over cherry filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling. Drizzle margarine on top and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 375° for one hour or until top lightly browned.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: brown stew(crock-pot)
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil in heavy skillet.
Drain off any excess oil. Combine meat, water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion, bay leaves, salt, pepper, allspice and sugar in crock-pot.
Cook on low for about 8 hours or on High for 6 hours.
After 2 hours of cooking, add the carrots and potatoes, scrubbed and cubed but not peeled. About 30 minutes before serving, add the bouillon cubes and green beans. Stir well.
Just before serving, combine cornstarch and water and add to stew to thicken the broth.

title: blueberry salad and topping
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple and pie filling.
Let congeal.

title: caramel candy
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk in a large saucepan. Combine butter, sugar, syrup and buttermilk in mixture, mixing well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage when tested in water.
Add vanilla and remove from heat.
Beat until it begins to harden.
Add pecans and beat.
Drop on oiled platter or wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In a bowl, sift together all dry ingredients.
Set aside.
In second bowl, cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs, milk, peanut butter and vanilla. Blend. Add dry ingredients to mixture and stir.
Shape dough into balls about 3/4-inch round.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately top each cookie with a chocolate kiss, pressing the kiss down firmly so cookie cracks around the edges.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Mix other ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Cool.

title: irish bread
directions: Grease and flour tube pan. Mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl (use mixer if desired).

Make a well or hole in the center of dry ingredients. Add liquid ingredients. Mix well with a wooden spoon until all the mixture is good and moist. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: super-supper casserole
directions: Turn into casserole and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken, broccoli and fusilli in garlic cream sauce
directions: Cook broccoli in a large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes.
Using slotted spoon, transfer broccoli to large bowl.
Add fusilli to same pot and cook until just tender but still firm to bite. Drain pasta.

title: cheese bread
directions: All ingredients need to be room temperature.
Whip together all ingredients until fluffy (15 minutes with electric mixer). Spread liberally on French or Italian bread and broil on rack.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix warm water and cocoa together until smooth.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: swedish cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add 1 cup of the sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Add cornstarch and 1/2 cup milk.
Now add the rest of the sugar, milk and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Set off and add oleo and vanilla.
Let cool.

title: oven-roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Arrange the vegetables in a large oiled baking dish and toss in the oil, butter, garlic and herbs. Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake for 35 minutes.
Uncover and turn the vegetables with a large spoon.
Add salt and pepper and roast at 425° for approximately 30 minutes or until the carrots and potatoes are thoroughly cooked and the edges of the vegetables have browned.
Serves 5.

title: mom's christmas jello
directions: Mix 1 box red Jell-O and 1 cup hot water.
Let jell; set aside.
Mix 1 box green Jell-O with all other ingredients except cream, then fold in cream after whipping.
Pour over red jello already set.
Mix box of red jello with 1 cup hot water.
Let cool, then pour over top.
Chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and carrots.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Stir in flour and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir together in a mixing bowl flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add vinegar, oil and cold water.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a greased square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh vegetables such as cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, celery, cucumbers, bell peppers, zucchini squash, radishes, etc.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer ingredients in the order listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: friendship cake starter mix(if you do not have the starter juice)
directions: If you have a starter juice for the Friendship Cake, then here is the recipe:

title: baked brie
directions: Bake in the microwave in a small Corning baking dish.
Serve as a spread for crackers.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; mix flour with sugar; cream with eggs.
Add butter, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Grease and flour 9-inch pie pan. Bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: holiday sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before frosting.
Serves 12.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican avocado dip
directions: Blend avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper together until all lumps are removed.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning mix together.
Heat refried beans and layer in bottom of glass baking dish.
Put a layer of avocado mix on top, then a layer of sour cream mix.
Then layer onion, tomatoes, black olives and cheese in same fashion.
Melt cheese in a 325° oven until desired consistency is obtained.

title: red hots
directions: Combine all ingredients through dill in medium size saucepan. Bring just to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer briefly. Serve in small mugs and garnish with parsley.
Makes 8 small cups.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry; pat in bottom and up sides of 8 x 2-inch quiche dish or 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cook and stir beef, onion and garlic in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Sprinkle with salt and flour.
Stir in pickle liquid, milk, pickles and 1 cup cheese.
Spoon into dish.
Bake 15 minutes; sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 5 minutes longer.
Use precooked pie shell.

title: apple crisp
directions: Ahead of time mix
apples,
cornstarch and brown sugar. Separately	mix
oil,
oatmeal
and
brown	sugar.	Put
apple mixture in Dutch oven and
cover with oatmeal topping mixture. Set on medium coals for 1 hour.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Put Crisco in a pan and lightly fry peppers and onions for 3 minutes.
Add meat and seasoning.
Remove from fire.
Stir in eggs.
Mix well.
Put one cup corn in baking dish, then half the meat mixture, then a layer of sliced tomatoes, then another layer of corn, meat and tomatoes.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.

title: kristina's cheese toast
directions: Use 3 mixing bowls.

title: * pea casserole *
directions: Toss the peas, mushrooms, cheese and cracker crumbs lightly. Put into 1-quart casserole.
Over this, pour the melted oleo and then the coffee cream.
Bake slowly at 275° for 1 hour.

title: pork and corn stuffing bake
directions: Combine soup, stuffing, celery, onion and paprika in a 9-inch greased pie plate.
Spoon stuffing.
Arrange chops on stuffing, pressing lightly into stuffing.
Combine sugar and mustard. Spread mixture evenly over chops.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: crabbies
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients; spread over muffins.
To make ahead, wrap individually and freeze.
When ready to use, cut into 6 to 8 pieces while still frozen.
Broil until crisp, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: linguine turkey bolognese
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients about 5 minutes.
Add turkey and brown slightly.
Add wine and simmer on low heat for 10 minutes. Add half and half; simmer until reduced, about 8 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano and broth.
Simmer, partially covered, for 1 hour.
Serve over pasta.
Contains 317 calories and 6 grams fat.

title: beef burgundy barbecue
directions: Combine marinade ingredients and add beef.
Let stand in sauce overnight.
Arrange meat and vegetables on skewers.
Cook over medium heat on grill.
Turn often and brush with marinade several times.
Tastes great with garlic bread!

title: spice raisin crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet.
Cream shortening with sugars.
Mix in eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and cloves.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Fold in Raisin Bran; drop by level tablespoon onto baking sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned.
Let stand 1 minute (only) before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine 4 cups flour, dry cake mix, yeast and warm water until smooth. Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a lightly floured surface, knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes. Punch dough down. Turn onto a lightly floured surface, divide in half. Roll each portion into a 14 x 10 inch rectangle, brush with butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Roll up jelly-roll style, starting with a long side. Cut each roll into 12 slices, place cut side down in two greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pans. Cover and let rise until almost doubled, about 20 minutes. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into large mixing bowl, beat until well mashed. Add remaining ingredients, blend, then beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into a well greased and floured 10 inch tube or bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan for at least 15 minutes.
Remove from pan, sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: broccoli with lemon and pepper
directions: Lightly steam broccoli until tender-crisp; drain.
While hot, sprinkle with lemon juice, pepper and grated lemon rind.
Add butter; toss lightly and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rhubarb meringue torte
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Add yolks and blend; press into oblong glass dish.

title: peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, stir together first 3 ingredients, stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, add cereal and toss to coat well.
Press into pan and let cool.
Then cut into squares.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter (add sugar slowly).
Add others until fluffy.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven add the bouillon cubes, carrots, onions, tomatoes, cabbage, corn, peas, bell pepper, okra, potatoes, celery and cooked stew beef. Add 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
If more water is desired, add.
Reduce heat to simmer and add 1 teaspoon black pepper, pinch of oregano, salt, garlic to taste, 1 bay leaf and a teaspoon of chili powder.
Cook until carrots and potatoes are done.
Serves 8.

title: chicken sauce piquant
directions: Wash and dry chicken and vegetables.
Dust chicken with salt, pepper and flour.
Brown chicken in vegetable oil.
Remove; drain. Remove skin from chicken and dispose of oil.
Fry bacon and reserve grease.
Drain bacon.
Make a brown roux.
Add chopped vegetables to roux and cook until clear.
Add tomatoes and broth and cook over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken back to pot.
Also return bacon after crumbled and season to taste. Cook until chicken is tender.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, cornbread stuffing, onion, garlic, chilies, egg, chili powder and half of the tomato sauce in a large pan.
Shape into a loaf and place in a shallow baking dish.
Add remaining tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: peach pudding
directions: Combine peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Place in baking dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour over peaches. Pour melted butter over all ingredients.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Dip a fork in sugar and crisscross, flattening cookies.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cookies are brown.

title: thanksgiving pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into a frozen pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lunch box muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: hamburger-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook beef in heated oil until brown, adding onions and peppers as beef starts to brown, stirring frequently to crumble beef. Drain off oil and fat; add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Stir into beef.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.
Pour macaroni into casserole dish and add hamburger mixture; stir.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 425° until cheese is melted.

title: better than sex
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, oleo and chopped nuts.
Press on bottom of 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dill biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut biscuits in half.
Dip each piece in butter mixture.
Arrange in a single layer on ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O using 3 cups water (set aside).
Grind 1 package raw cranberries.
Grind 2 oranges with peeling.
Add 2 cups sugar. Mix well.
Add the celery and nuts.
Stir in the Jell-O.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken le marie
directions: Combine crumbs and cheese.
Reserve half.
Dip chicken in crumbs and place in baking dish.
Cook onions and butter.
Blend flour and milk into onion mixture.
Cook until thick.
Stir spinach and ham into sauce mixture.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese you have reserved over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: miniature fruit cake
directions: Chop pecans, dates, cherries and pineapple.
Combine first four ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, baking soda (or baking powder) and salt together.
Add to chopped nuts and fruits and mix well, using hands.
Beat eggs until foamy; add to mixture and blend well.
Pour melted butter over mixture and mix well.
Pack mixture into small paper baking cups placed in muffin tins.
Fill cups full.
Bake at 300° about 40 minutes.
Makes 32.

title: calypso breeze punch
directions: Freeze Calypso Breeze cartons and chill ginger ale.
Set frozen cartons out about two hours before serving.
When ready to serve; just pour ginger ale over the Calypso Breeze in punch bowl and stir until slushy.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: hattie's sugar cookies
directions: Roll out dough 18-inches and cut with a cookie cutter.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients together well.
Sift next 4 together and add alternately with next ingredient.
Follow Solomon's advice for a good boy Proverbs 23:14.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Fold in beaten yolks and stiffly beaten whites carefully.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch lined pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place rice and broccoli in 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in half of the cheese.
Melt butter in skillet (I use less than 1 cup).
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in soup and milk.
Season to taste.
Pour sauce over broccoli-rice mixture; mix well.
Top casserole with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered mint chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with 1 cup sweetened condensed milk and add vanilla.
Spread half the mixture into a waxed paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: crock-pot turkey chili
directions: In a large skillet, cook turkey, onion and garlic in oil until meat loses pink color.
Add dry spices; heat well.
Pour into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on high 30 minutes; turn to low and cook (many) hours.

title: cranberry mince pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position in oven.
Preheat oven to 425°.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain off grease.
Spoon beef into a
8 inch baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine Bisquick mix, egg and milk and beat until smooth.
Pour mixture over casserole covering evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: beef roast
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over roast.
Bake, covered, 3 to 4 hours in a 350° oven.

title: seven-up lime punch
directions: Spoon 3 pints sherbet into punch bowl.
Soften for about 5 minutes at room temperature.
Then slowly pour in chilled 7-Up, stirring slightly.
Float remaining sherbet on top of punch. Makes about 36 cups.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Place noodles in a large casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over noodles and top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.

title: orange-sugared nuts
directions: Boil sugar and orange juice until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from fire; add rind and nut halves.
Stir until turns cloudy.
Pour on cookie sheet and separate nuts with fork.

title: chocolate cake with fudge frosting
directions: Bake cakes and cool.
Whip the whipping cream; add 1/4 cup powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Spread whipped cream between layers of cake.
Refrigerate while making frosting.

title: decadent chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Pour boiling water over chocolate and butter; let stand until melted.
Stir in vanilla and sugar, then whisk in egg yolks, one at a time; blend well after each addition.
Mix baking soda and sour cream; whisk into chocolate mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to batter, mixing well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir 1/4 of the egg whites into batter.
Scoop remaining whites on top of batter and fold in.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Place on middle rack in oven and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; unmold and cool completely. Frost.

title: crab salad in pineapple shells
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss all ingredients except pineapple; cover and refrigerate.
Cut pineapple in half lengthwise; scoop out pineapple, leaving 1/2 inch thick shells.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cut scooped pineapple into chunks; toss into crab mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: yummy pie
directions: Stir condensed milk and lemon juice together.
Add pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into crust.
Makes 2 large 9-inch pies.
Should be frozen for at least two hours before serving.
Great dessert to make "way" ahead of time.

title: green chili enchilada casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook beef with onion and bell pepper.
Set aside.
Heat tortillas, one at a time, until soft.
Set aside and keep warm.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour until smooth and add milk.
When milk and flour are hot, add Velveeta and green chilies.
When smooth, arrange tortillas in casserole dish; one at a time, fill with ground beef and grated Cheddar or Colby cheese.
Roll each one.
When casserole pan is full, pour sauce over tortillas.
Cover tortillas with sauce and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble 1/2 cornbread and spread in glass bowl.
Top with 1/2 vegetable mix.
Layer again and top with bacon over second vegetables that are on top.
Cover and put in refrigerator 6 hours or overnight.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Parboil chicken and cut into pieces.
In large mixing bowl, combine chicken, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and broccoli. Mix together.
Place above ingredients in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Crush crackers and combine with butter.
Sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix with mayonnaise.
Serve with crackers.

title: real good taffy apples(candied apples)
directions: Wash and dry apples; remove stems.
Insert wooden sticks into stem end of apples; set aside.

title: golfer's chicken
directions: Combine dry soup, Russian dressing and jam.
Mix well until there are no lumps.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Slightly overlap chicken in dish and spoon sauce on all.
Cook 1 hour at 375° or 4 hours at 225°.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in skillet.
Mix milk and 2 egg yolks. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Add vanilla, sugar-flour mixture and milk-egg mixture to caramelized sugar.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thick and not lumpy.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites; sweeten and top pie.
Brown at 350°.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine and shake vigorously in a bottle.

title: bits 'o brickle bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg and press in pan.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, 1 egg, pecans, Brickle chips and vanilla.
Pour over cake mixture in pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine. Add all ingredients. Mix well. Place in casserole dish. Top with crackers. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot and pineapple coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pineapple chunks, carrots and almonds in a large bowl; toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Pour dressing mixture over cabbage mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, bread,
milk,
salt
and	pepper in large bowl. Add beef,
cheese,	carrots and onion; shape into loaf. Place into lightly greased
dish
(use glass pan if cooking in microwave). Bake for
minutes in microwave oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 50 minutes if cooked in regular oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add mashed bananas, vanilla and eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients (except nuts) and add to first mixture.
Stir only until well mixed, then add nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados; add lemon juice and mix with bean dip.
Spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix together and spread over bean dip mixture.
Dice tomatoes and olives and sprinkle along with cheese on top.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Stir in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix
flour and shortening together.
Add milk, salt and baking powder.
Roll
thin
and spread Crisco over top.
Fold together and
cut
biscuits
out of folded dough or drop biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue easy and delicious
directions: Salt roast and boil until tender.
Let cool to touch and tear into small pieces.
Heat in skillet or broiler and add your favorite barbecue sauce, stirring constantly until all meat is covered with sauce and meat is hot.

title: c and c casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower and carrots separately in salted water until slightly crunchy.
Place in buttered casserole.
Mix soup and milk; pour over veggies.
Blend butter and crackers; sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soup, in a large bowl; blend well.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Pour cream of mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mack chops
directions: Put 2 tablespoons olive oil in frying pan.
Sprinkle pork chop with dill weed, rubed sage, salt and pepper.
Place in pan.
Put 2 tablespoons wine on each pork chop.
Cook until brown.
Turn and repeat on other side.

title: jenna's favorite fruit soup
directions: Put orange juice into bowl. Add the yogurt, honey and lemon juice. Use a small whisk to mix the ingredients. Slice the banana into the soup. Add the berries. Ladle and eat for breakfast or a quick light summer lunch.

title: vegetarian chopped liver *
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Chop all ingredients and mix together well.
Serves 6.

title: pastry
directions: Cut shortening into flour until particles are size of small peas.
Sprinkle in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing with a fork until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans side of bowl (1 to 2 teaspoons water can be added, if necessary).

title: magic pork chops
directions: Score fat on chops.
Brush mayonnaise on both sides of each pork chop.
Drizzle seasoned bread crumbs on both sides of each chop.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Bake on rack in shallow roasting pan at 375° for 35 minutes.
This is also good for chicken parts as well.

title: french onion soup
directions: Combine water, bouillon, onions, salt and pepper.
Boil until onions are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Float in each bowl a piece of toast topped with melted butter, garlic, powder and Parmesan cheese mixture which has been browned in oven and cut in cubes.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Brown the chuck and sausage together; drain excess oil.
Add the spices, onions and pepper which have been chopped fine.
Cook until onions and pepper are soft; then stir in Velveeta cheese. Heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on 3 or 4 loaves of party Rye bread.
This can now be frozen if necessary.
When ready to eat, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 450° oven for 10-15 minutes.
Yum-m-m Good!
This recipe is from a Cajun friend in Louisiana.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown meat with onion, bell pepper and celery.
Drain.
Boil water.
Add rice and soup and boil 7 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients to water, rice and soup.
Pour in casserole dish, cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pie filling in bottom of baking dish.
Next, put drained pineapple, then dry cake mix, then coconut, then melted butter. Bake until brown (about 30 minutes) at 350°.

title: slaw
directions: Coarsely chop 1 head of cabbage.
Mix remainder of ingredients together and stir into cabbage right before serving.

title: creole cream  cheese cheesecake
directions: To make the crust, preheat the oven to 225°. Break up the crackers and grind them into a fine meal in a blender or food processor or under a rolling pin. In a large bowl, blend together the crumbs, butter and sugar. Press into the bottom and sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: stew for all occasions
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 5 or 6-quart Dutch oven or crock-pot. Cover and bake for about 3 hours, stirring twice, until beef is tender and sauce thickens.
(Remove bay leaves.)
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy day dinner
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix together; fold in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: eggs in snow
directions: Toast bread on one side.
Toast underside very lightly. Butter lightly toasted side.
Keep hot.
Add seasonings and pinch of nutmeg to egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Spread over buttered toast.
Make slight indentation in middle; drop in egg yolk. Sprinkle with cheese.
Put under hot broiler a few minutes until egg yolk has set.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Very important to bake over a pan of water at 350° for 70 to 80 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl, combine the beef, egg white, onion, crumbs, milk, horseradish, salt and pepper. Shape into 4 oval patties. Fry in skillet over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes or until cooked through, turning once. Remove patties and keep warm. Add gravy, mushrooms and water to skillet. Heat 3 to 5 minutes. Serve over patties and noodles, if desired.

title: one dish-pork chop dinner
directions: In frying pan, melt Crisco.
Brown pork chops on both sides. Pour out excess grease.
Combine all ingredients.
Add the water to cover rice and pork chops.
Cover with lid.
Let simmer on medium heat for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Add chopped onion.
Mix together.
Mix well all ingredients with bean mixture.
Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.
Can keep in refrigerator for several days.
Flavor improves with age.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mash sauce with fork and bring to a boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved. Add cold water and salt. Chill mixture until partially thick.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour in mold. Let chill.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook in a heavy saucepan.
Color may be added to the water and oil.
Stir constantly until stiff and dough pulls from sides of pan.
Knead until smooth, then keep in a closed container.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Remove skin and debone chicken.
Dice into large pieces.
Put Doritos into a bowl and pour broth over them.
Let stand 5 minutes, stirring often.
Grease a large casserole dish.

title: roasted red peppers
directions: Slice peppers into halves and remove the seeds.
Place peppers onto a lightly greased pan and put them into the oven.
Roast the peppers until the skins feel dry and are all puckered, then let cool and peel the skins off.
Place the peppers, garlic and portions of oil into a jar, making sure the peppers are covered. Allow this to marinate for at least 3 hours, after which they will be ready to use.

title: potato salad(microwave)
directions: Place potatoes, water and salt in 4-quart microproof casserole.
Cover and place in microwave oven.
Cook on High 8 minutes.
Stir, cover and cook on High 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; drain.
Pour dressing over potatoes; toss lightly.
Set aside 1/4 cup egg for garnish.
Add remaining eggs to potatoes; toss lightly.
Set aside 1 tablespoon pimiento for garnish; add remaining pimiento to potato mixture.
Blend in mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon into serving bowl. Garnish with reserved egg, pimiento and parsley.
Serves 6.
A very pleasant new taste for potato salad.
Takes 16 minutes cooking time.

title: old-fashion bread pudding
directions: Combine hot milk with bread cubes and butter.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Beat eggs; add salt, sugar and vanilla and beat until well blended.
Add bread mixture.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° the last 10 to 15 minutes to retain moisture.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, butter, egg, 1/2 (8 ounce) cream cheese and milk.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Place peaches in a single layer on top of batter.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and peach juice. Beat for 2 minutes.
Spoon on top of peaches within 1-inch of the edge of batter.
Mix remaining tablespoon sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until light brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cook all ingredients in large skillet until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust (9-inch).

title: sneaky squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Spread half of stuffing in bottom of casserole.
Layer chicken over stuffing.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinade
directions: Used on chicken is best.
But you can marinate any kind of meat you like.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add butter and eggs.
Mix well by hand.
Add vanilla and evaporated milk.
Mix with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tropical punch cooler
directions: In blender container or food processor bowl with metal blade, combine 2 tablespoons of the powdered sugar, 3/4 cup of the water, 1 package peach slices and 1 can orange juice concentrate.
Blend until smooth.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mash avocado and mix with pineapple to help hold color.
Mix jello, water and lemon juice.
Let set to jelly stage.
Whip cream; add Miracle Whip.
Fold into jello. Add avocado/pineapple mixture.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip, condensed milk and vanilla until mixed well.
Spread bottom of a two-quart casserole with pudding.
Cover with layer of vanilla wafers.
Top with layer of sliced bananas.
Continue to layer pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas.
End with pudding on top.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix well.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: peach chutney
directions: Grind first five ingredients.
Simmer all 1 or 2 hours, until thick.
Pour into 4 hot pint jars. Seal.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix with flour, vinegar, egg and sugar. Cook until thick.
Cool completely and mix with Cool Whip. Fold in apples, peanuts and pineapple. Best if made the night before serving.
Keeps well.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix 1 cup flour and 1 stick butter.
Pat it in a pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop popcorn; set aside in large bowl.
Combine next 6 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture reaches hard ball stage (260°).
Remove from heat; add butter, stirring until butter melts.
Pour syrup in a thin stream over popcorn, stirring until popcorn is evenly coated.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Press mixture into a well-greased ring mold; cool.
Unmold on serving plate.

title: steak and dressing
directions: Cut cubed steak into small pieces and set aside.
Cook grits until done.
In a mixing bowl, place bread and pour enough hot water over to make soft.
Using potato masher, mash bread until it becomes soft. Add all other ingredients except the steak.
Mix well. Spray dish with cooking spray.
Layer dressing and steak beginning and ending with dressing.
Place in 350 degree oven for 1-1/2 hours or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water and add lemon juice.
Then add relish and pineapple.
Chill until slightly firm and add celery, apple and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Will serve 12.
May be made a day ahead.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour and add dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with sugar, oil, egg yolks and hot water.
Mix the grated carrots, then the nuts to batter, then fold in the egg white.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: grated noodles(reszelt teszta)
directions: Mix flour and eggs by hand and form a hard ball.
Grate on large side of potato grater.
Spread out on waxed paper to dry.

title: twice-baked sweet potatoes
directions: Remove center of sweet potatoes, leaving boat-shaped center. Mix centers and other ingredients together.
Refill potatoes and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Brush melted oleo on top and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Serves 4.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Put popped corn, nuts and M&M's in large bowl.
Simmer margarine, oil and marshmallows until the marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool 5 minutes, then pour cooked mixture over popped corn, nuts and M&M's.
Stir until well mixed.
Press mixture into a greased angel food 10-inch tube cake pan.
Let set several hours and turn upside down on cake plate.
Cut with bread knife.

title: fluffy lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve juice). Set aside. In saucepan, combine jello, water and reserved juice. Cook and stir over low heat until jello is dissolved. Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add vanilla, butter, salt, sugar and Karo syrup; blend well.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and continue baking until pie is firm to the touch.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in an unbaked pie shell. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Place powdered sugar and peanut butter in Tupperware bowl and seal; shake.
Mixture will form small balls.
Save 1/2 cup and place remainder in pie shell.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Cook chicken, reserve 1 cup broth.
Cut up chicken and layer in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Thin soup with broth and pour over chicken layer.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken.
Prepare stuffing mix per directions.
Spread on top of cheese layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple-vanilla pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until firm.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix together Marshmallow
Creme
and cream cheese;
add enough pineapple juice to thin down.
Good to dip all kinds of fruit (apples, grapes, bananas).

title: creamy pralines
directions: Boil sugar, water, milk and syrup slightly (no problem if curdling occurs).
Add pecans.
Cook until firm ball forms in cold water, 240° to 242° on candy thermometer.
Takes about 35 minutes. Remove from heat and add butter, margarine and vanilla.
Beat until it loses shiny look, about 15 minutes.
Drop on greased or foil covered baking sheets (at least two); work fast.
Makes about 35 pieces.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pull apart bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix oil, boiling water, sugar and egg.
Mix well; add dissolved yeast to this and mix. Now add salt to flour, adding 1 cup flour at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Put mixture in greased mixing bowl and cover.
Set in warm place; let rise until double in size.
Make rolls; let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in boiling water for 8 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup, water chestnuts (drained and sliced) and green pepper.
Add celery.
Mix.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs mixed with melted butter and slivered almonds if you prefer.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: layered seafood salad
directions: In 2 1/2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, pea pods, peppers, cucumbers and crab meat.
Mix well, adding sugar and dill to salad dressing.
Spread over top of salad to seal.
Chill overnight. Enjoy!

title: raspberry pie
directions: Cook 1 cup of raspberries with water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Mix remaining 3 cups of berries and pour into baked pie shell.

title: angel food cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, pineapple with juice and lemon juice. Chill, but not solid, sort of juicy.
Whip 2 packages Dream Whip and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Break cake into 15 x 4 x 2-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 gelatin mixture in.
Add another layer of cake pieces.
Add rest of gelatin mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Whip third package of Dream Whip and spread on top. Chill.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie("so good!")
directions: Bake pie crust according to package directions. Set aside. In a medium saucepan, combine pudding mix, gelatin mix and water. Stir to dissolve; continue stirring over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil. Remove from heat. Cool glaze in refrigerator until slightly thickened. Arrange strawberries in pie shell. Pour cooled glaze over strawberries. Chill and eat.

title: tanya's loaf bread
directions: Add flour to other ingredients a cup at a time. Blend all ingredients with a mixer until dough crawls up the beaters. Work in the rest of the flour by hand. Work in just enough flour to make a good dough. Let rise in a greased pan until double in size. Punch down. Place in 5 greased loaf pans and let rise until double. Bake at 325°. If using small loaf pans, bake for 45 minutes. Bake in large loaf pans for 55 minutes.

title: sesame dressing
directions: Blend thoroughly.
Serve on salads with toasted sesame or almonds.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Follow recipe from cake mix.
Make sheet cake.
Cut according to diagram.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly, add oleo, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat again until well blended.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into pie pan and it forms its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: First put in your casserole a layer of cooked cubed potatoes, then a main layer of cooked noodles.
Next a layer of cooked cut up chicken.
Now a layer of bread crumbs.
Pour over all a chicken gravy, making it thin enough so your casserole will not be too dry when done.
Bake in oven until top is browned.

title: date nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar.
Stir in crushed saltines, dates, pecans and almond flavoring.
Bake in preheated oven at 270° for 1 hour.
The pan must be well-greased. It is best to draw the batter to the outside of the pan.
When cool, cut in wedges.
Serve with a scoop of ice cream.

title: oatmeal coconut crispies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Blend flour, soda and salt thoroughly; stir into shortening mixture.
Blend in rolled oats and coconut (dough will be soft).
Shape in two rolls, each about 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper; refrigerate overnight. Heat oven to 400°.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip creme pies
directions: Prepare and bake 32 cookies according to package directions. Mix marshmallow creme and powdered sugar.
Knead mixture into a "cookie dough roll".
Slice into 18 slices and place between two cookies.
Serve warm.

title: "layered lettuce salad"
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in large salad bowl. Mix mayonnaise and sugar or Splenda. Spread over the top of salad to seal. Let set overnight in refrigerator. Before serving, sprinkle cheese and bacon bits on top.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place
a
wire rack large enough to hold chicken in a baking dish or pan.
(Dish may be lined with foil for easy
cleaning.)
Mix
bread crumbs and seasonings on waxed paper. Pull skin	off
chicken
and cut off excess fat. Use fingertips to	coat chicken with yogurt.
Press chicken in crumbs mixture, then
turn to coat completely.
Place on rack, leaving space between
pieces.
Bake
45	to
50 minutes until coating is lightly browned
and
juices run clear when meat is pierced with tip of a knife.

title: chow chow
directions: Bring last 7 ingredients to boil.
Add vegetables.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and tighten lids (will seal themselves).
Recipe can be divided.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let simmer at least 1 hour.

title: beef soup
directions: Place meat and bones in pot; cover with water (approximately 8 to 10 cups).
Bring to a boil.
Skim off fat from top of soup. Add chopped celery, onion and carrots.
Smash tomatoes and add to pot.
Add salt to taste.
Add parsley.
Cover.
Boil on low temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
Add noodles or rice.
Cook for approximately 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: california caesar salad(preparation time: 10 minutes)
directions: In cup, combine dressing and mustard.
In large bowl, combine lettuce, carrots and onions.
Pour dressing mixture over lettuce mixture; toss to coat.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Cook hamburg with a little onion.
Add taco mix and water; cook down a bit and add beans.
Put 1 layer of Fritos or Doritos in a jelly roll pan and pour hot meat sauce over it.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with green pepper and chopped tomato.

title: cranberry cocktail
directions: Wash cranberries; cook with water until skins pop open, about 5 minutes. Strain. Bring juice to boiling point. Add sugar and cook about 2 minutes. Chill and serve.

title: onion seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over broken pretzels.
Bake 45 minutes at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine the powdered sugar and peanut butter until texture is of coarse meal.
Put 3/4 of the mixture in a baked 9-inch pastry shell.
Combine rest of ingredients in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.

title: savory tomato quick bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salts, oregano, sugar and cheeses.
Add enough milk to drained tomato liquid to make 2/3 cup.
Blend liquid with eggs and oil.
Stir liquid and chopped tomatoes into flour mixture until thoroughly moistened.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 75 to 80 minutes.
If bread is brown before baking time is complete, cover with a foil tent.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and turn onto wire rack and cool thoroughly.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour gradually, beating each time.
Add vanilla and nuts and blend.
Shape into crescents; place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in single layer in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade and grill 20 minutes.

title: club cracker toffee
directions: Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil.
Line with Club crackers.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring butter, margarine and brown sugar to a full, rolling boil for about 1 to 2 minutes. Immediately pour over Club crackers.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350° or until corners start to turn brown.
Remove from pan.
Place Hershey chocolate bars on top (spaced) and spread evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press rolls in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook bacon or sausage.
Drain.
Sprinkle this over rolls.
Sprinkle cheese over bacon.
Combine the eggs, milk and pepper.
Pour over the cheese. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Bring water and salt to rapid boil.
Add lasagne without breaking them.
Stir and separate them and boil for 15 minutes. Drain and rinse to prevent sticking.
In buttered baking dish, bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Brown meat with onion.
Pour off grease.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and whole tomatoes along with oregano, minced garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Place 3 cooked noodles in bottom of low baking dish (buttered).
Over this layer of noodles, spread sauce to cover, then spread Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Layer more noodles, more sauce and the 3 cheeses.
When all ingredients have been layered, add tomato juice to liquify.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot!

title: arabic upside-down chicken
directions: Cut and wash cauliflower.
Boil chicken in water with small amounts of allspice, nutmeg, cinnamon and a small piece of lemon. Wash or soak rice for about 10 minutes.
Put olive oil, cumin, garlic salt and regular salt in bottom of casserole dish (season to taste).
Put chicken in casserole dish, then cauliflower, then rice and pour broth from chicken over ingredients, adding water if needed to cover completely.
Dot with butter and cook in oven on high for about 10 minutes, then lower heat to medium-high and cook until rice is tender.

title: long john silver batter
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add last 2 ingredients. Dip fish, chicken or onion rings into batter.
Fry in a deep fryer.

title: blackberry or strawberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Beat until well mixed, then pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour berries over mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until crust rises to the top and browns.

title: hummus
directions: Sprinkle with paprika or parsley if you wish before serving.

title: apple dumpling pastry
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and roll out to fit a 9 x 12-inch pan. Leave enough to fold over top.
Peel and slice enough apples to fill pan about half full.
Sprinkle sugar over apples and fold dough over top of apples.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Combine corn, soup and melted margarine; mix well.
Stir in cooked yellow rice.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake until cheese is brown.

title: low calorie chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Add cornstarch and spices.
Add tomato juice and water; simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Add shredded cabbage the last hour.
The long simmering brings out the flavor.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: tomato and rice soup
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in Dutch oven until brown (about 5 minutes).
Drain fat and add remaining ingredients, except green beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add green beans.
Adjust seasonings.
Better if made a day ahead.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Dip eggplant into beaten egg, then in flour mixture.
In a large skillet, brown eggplant in hot oil. Drain on paper towel.
Place 1 layer of eggplant in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with half the Parmesan cheese.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: In a saucepan, beat egg slightly.
Stir in milk, sugar, margarine and
salt.
Cook	and stir over medium heat about 12 minutes or	until
thickened
and bubbly.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Cool
thoroughly.	Spread	on
cake.
Frosts top of 1 (13 x 9-inch) cake or tops of 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers.

title: chocolate mint torte
directions: Prepare crust and let cool. Fill with the following:
Beat butter until creamy. Add sugar. Beat until light and fluffy. Beat in chocolate, vanilla and peppermint.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, 3 minutes each.
Fold in whipped cream. Garnish with grated chocolate.
Chill overnight or 4 hours minimum.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Mix soup, 1/2 cup cheese, pepper, and chicken. Place tortilla on 2 baking sheets. Top half of each tortilla with 1/4 cup soup mixture. Spread to within 1/2 inch of edge. Moisten edges with water to seal. Fold over and press edges together. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until hot. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil . When rice starts to brown, stir in bell pepper, onion and garlic. Meanwhile in a bowl, put the chicken bouillon, Spanish rice seasoning, cumin seed, garlic powder and pepper. Put water and salt in microwave to boil. Put Ro-Tel and add all spices in boiling water; pour over rice. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cover. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sliced pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in mild salt solution using 1/2 cup salt. Drain well.
Boil the syrup made with remaining ingredients for 5 minutes.
Can while hot in sterilized jars.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Spread chopped pecans on aluminum foil or on the countertop in about a 12-inch square.
Put softened cream cheese into large mixing bowl and add all other ingredients.
Mix all together with hands and shape into a ball.
Roll ball in chopped pecans until it is all covered.
Drop in a pretty bowl and chill for 1 hour. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: norma's hot rolls
directions: Combine yeast and warm water and stir until yeast is dissolved.
Add salt and sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients at once.
Mix well (use hands if necessary). Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and form into any type roll desired.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix and put into jar.
Use 3 to 4 teaspoons with 1 cup of hot water.

title: odessa's asparagus casserole
directions: Crush crackers and grate the cheese and mix together and set aside.
Grease a casserole dish with oleo or butter.
Put a layer of crackers and cheese in the bottom of the dish.
Put half this mixture for the teaspoon.
Drain the asparagus and liquids together.
Place the asparagus over the layers of crackers and cheese.
Spread the cream of mushroom soup mixture over the layers of asparagus.
Add the rest of the crackers and cheese mixture. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix potatoes, milk, 1/3 c. butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Pour into 2 quart casserole.
Mix coconut, brown sugar, 1/3 c. melted butter and pecans; sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, sour cream and mushroom soup together. Melt margarine and pour over dressing; mix together.
Put 1/2 of the dressing into a casserole dish and add the squash mixture. Put the other 1/2 of dressing on top of squash mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour or until golden.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream lard and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in soda and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls, flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take 1 cup pineapple juice (you can add a little orange juice if you do not have a full cup of pineapple juice).
Add Tang and instant pudding.
Mix well and add to fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: one-step lasagne
directions: Microwave the ground beef until no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and the salt.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, layer 1/3 of the sauce, 1/2 of uncooked noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese and 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover tightly and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish. Microwave on 70% powder for 20 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Additional cheese may be sprinkled on top after baking, if desired.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat the butter or margarine until fluffy.
Add sugar, flour and vanilla; beat until blended.
Add chopped nuts.
Fold potato chips into batter.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while cookies are still warm.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly brown.

title: sweet green tomato and corn piccalilli
directions: Rub tomato slices with salt and allow to stand covered overnight in refrigerator.
Squeeze tomato slices between layers of cheesecloth to remove excess moisture.
Set aside.
In a large sauce pan, combine vinegar, sugar, cloves and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add reserved tomatoes, stir well.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
This will keep well, covered and refrigerated, for several weeks.

title: chanukah rolls
directions: In saucepan bring 1 cup of water and prunes to boil; reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Drain and mash prunes.
Add cinnamon, orange peel, lemon juice, sugar and butter; mix well.

title: chinese asparagus
directions: Cut asparagus diagonally in 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add asparagus and sprinkle with salt. Cover pan and cook 3 minutes, or until fork-tender.
Serve topped with slivered almonds (optional).

title: peach pie
directions: Mix milk, flour, sugar and 1 teaspoon of melted butter, then add peaches to mixture.
Pour into greased glass baking pan. Slice 1 stick butter over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry salad(serves 10)
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Mix and add other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and put Ro-Tel and cheese together until melted with hamburger.
Pour in bowl or small crock-pot.
Eat with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: chicken a la tortillas
directions: Boil chicken until tender, cool and chop.
Make a sauce with soups, onions, peppers, celery and 3/4 of cheese.
Mix chopped chicken into sauce.
Place strips of tortillas into baking dish, cover with 1/2 of sause.
Add another layer of tortilla strips and the rest of the sauce.
Top with the rest of the cheese.
Bake for 30 mins. at 350 degrees.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions and cook 3 minutes or until yellow.
Add broth, salt, and pepper.
Cook slowly 20 minutes or until onions are tender.
Do not cover.
Serve with croutons and grated parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Cook pudding with 2 cups of milk.
Mix cake right from the box into pudding.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread on top the butterscotch morsels.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pauline's dog chow(not for dogs)
directions: Melt together margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Drizzle over and stir into the Rice Chex. Dump powdered sugar into paper bag.
Pour cereal mix into paper bag and shake well.

title: banana bread
directions: Assemble in order given and stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Pour into bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine Quick Mix and liquid.
Blend. Let stand 2 or 3 minutes.
On lightly floured board, knead 10 to 15 times.
Pat out about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with a floured cutter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes on unbuttered pan.
Makes 12 large biscuits.

title: baked chicken stir-fry
directions: Brown outside of chicken in garlic oil (do not cook).
Set aside in casserole dish.
In same frying pan as chicken and oil, stir-fry onion, carrots, celery and garlic until onion are clear in color.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and vegetables are a little crunchy.
Serve over rice.

title: "ginger snaps" molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Mix together ingredients and chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Shape into balls and dip the tops in sugar.
Do not press down.
Bake until tops crack but not dry.
Bake at 350°.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix by hand cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Pat in greased, buttered pan.
Mix, using mixer, powdered sugar, 3 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, brown meat with onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in remaining ingredients, bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
If zucchini is available, I add a cup of chopped zucchini.

title: pizza dough with beer(for bread machine)
directions: Place beer, butter, sugar and salt into baking pan.
Add flour.
Sprinkle yeast into center of flour.
Close lid.
Select "dough" bread setting.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Beat eggs with buttermilk and melted butter. Combine dry and wet ingredients; do not overmix. Heat butter in skillet over medium heat. Spoon 1/3 cup of batter into skillet. Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Serve with whipped cream and syrup.

title: favorite recipe
directions: Take I-20 east to I-75/I-85 Atlanta interchange.
Exit International Blvd.
Turn right into Steak and Ale and enjoy.

title: oven fried chicken and biscuits
directions: On wax paper, mix potato flakes, seasonings and cheese.
In pie plate, mix egg with 1 teaspoon water.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll in potato flake mixture.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Grease a 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and line with 3 layers of waxed paper.
Set oven at 325°.
Into bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in chocolate, walnuts and fruits.
In another bowl, beat eggs well. Gradually beat in sugar. Fold in flour mixture.
Pour into pans. Bake 1 1/2 hours in preheated oven.

title: crab ring
directions: In a saucepan dissolve gelatine in 3 tablespoons water.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cream cheese, let melt slowly over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ring mold.
Chill overnight or until set. Serve with crackers or celery as a dip, or as a main dish.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl and beat until smooth.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice
directions: Grease a 3 1/2-quart crock-pot.
Combine soup (undiluted), mushrooms and juice, onion soup mix and rice in pot.
Lay chicken breasts on top of mixture. Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 9 hours. Serves 4 to 6.

title: stromboli
directions: My mother was a very busy woman, as there were 10 children to feed each day.
She baked 25 pounds of flour into bread every other day.
If her batch of bread wasn't baked when we dashed home for lunch, she would make fried bread for us.
She would take a chunk of raised dough, slice it and pull it flat and fry it in deep olive oil.
When it was brown and crisp, she put it on a platter and sprinkled with sugar.
It didn't last long!!

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix all together and roll into finger shapes.
Bake at 350° until they begin to brown slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar. These keep well stored in covered container.

title: baked haddock with shrimp stuffing
directions: Grease pan and add fish.
Spread soup and shrimp on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Combine butter, seasonings, grated onion and crackers.
Sprinkle over fish and bake 10 minutes more.

title: never fail pie meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and salt.
Cook in small saucepan until clear.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until frothy. Continue beating while pouring in cooked mixture.
Continue beating 5 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Combine soup and tomatoes in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle each serving with chips and cheese.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook for 12 minutes and stir after 5 minutes.
Cook until 12 minutes are up and stir again.
Then add nuts and cook 12 more minutes or until it starts to brown.
Stir after 3 minutes are up and check every 3 minutes after.
When done, add butter and soda. Pour onto 4 aluminum sheets.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in paper cups in muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: ambrosia(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Blend ingredients.
This fruit medley can be frozen in a mold or served traditionally on a bed of greens.

title: gar bowlette balls
directions: Grind bacon, celery, garlic and onions.
Mix well with garfish, pepper, salt and potatoes.
Add 2 eggs; mix real good.
Make 2-inch balls and pat into patties or leave as a ball.
Use flour to roll them in and fry in hot oil.
Makes 65 or 75 depending on size.

title: chinese tea balls
directions: Cream butter with mixer.
Stir in pecans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with hands and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Arrange potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in orange juice.
Add raisins.
Stir while bringing to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; wash caps and drain.
Microwave caps until tender and drain all water.
Saute chopped onions and mushroom stems in butter until tender; drain and mix with melted cheeses.
Add sour cream and prepared bacon; salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff in caps and eat immediately.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and keep in airtight container.
Sometimes I throw in a handful of red hots (cinnamon hearts) for color.
To serve, add a heaping spoonful of mixture to boiling water in a mug and stir.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add sauce mix, sauce, sugar, butter and 2 cups water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook manicotti noodles 10 to 15 minutes only.
Add oil to water while cooking.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Stuff with mixture of cheeses, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Layer in casserole.
Pour sauce over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown pie crust.
Put in hamburger meat mixed with taco seasoning.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: parmesan round steak
directions: Trim fat from steak and cut into serving size pieces.
Combine egg and milk and beat well.
Combine breadcrumbs, salt, pepper and Accent.
Dip steak in egg mixture; dredge in breadcrumbs and brown in bacon drippings.
Place steak in lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Add water and sprinkle with oregano and cheese.
Then add onions; sprinkle with remaining salt and paprika.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: caramel squares
directions: Melt
margarine
and
sugar
in double boiler or on low heat. Add
eggs
and beat well. Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Beat
until
smooth.
Stir in pecans. Pour into greased and
floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut in small squares.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Coat broccoli, mushrooms, cauliflower, ripe olives, carrots, celery, etc.
Let marinate at least 1 day.

title: diabetic blueberry muffin
directions: Mix egg, milk and oil in one bowl.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder,
then add to egg mixture until moist.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour	into greased muffin (or use Pam).
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: phinadiny
directions: Marinate (use enough marinade to cover) meat (chicken, pork chops or steak) 30 minutes to overnight.
Grill on barbecue until done.

title: special pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together the oleo or butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat thoroughly; mix in pumpkin and water.
Combine in separate bowl the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well; stir dry ingredients into pumpkin a little at a time, stirring until batter is well blended.
Stir in cherries and walnuts. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
