Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Mix together 3 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Blend in 1/2 cup butter or margarine.
Add 2 cups very warm water and stir.
Add 1 cup flour and stir, then add egg.
Mix in rest of flour and knead for 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover with a light towel and let rise for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Turn out on floured board and punch down.
Let rest for 15 minutes.
While waiting, melt 1/2 cup butter and pour into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Divide dough in half and roll out until 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in circles of about 3 inches.
Dip in butter and fold in half in pan.
Let rise for about 1 1/2 hours. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for approximately 20 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: weekend casserole
directions: Cook chicken, celery and onion until tender.
Spray large, oblong baking dish with Pam.
Put drained spaghetti in dish.
Top with chicken, celery and onion.
Combine soups in bowl and whisk until blended.
(May need to add a bit of milk.)
Pour over spaghetti and chicken.
Layer cheese over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond chicken pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken, apples, cooked pasta, pineapple, grape, celery
and onions.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Seven-Up, pudding mix, Crisco oil and eggs. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed with mixer.
Bake in 3 layer pan or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° until golden brown.
Cool and frost.

title: small layer cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Cream together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate flour and buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 4 greased and wax paper-lined layer pans.
Makes four thick layers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: campfire grilled onions
directions: Cut onions into wedges. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over onions. Put on thick foil or double layer foil. Fold foil to seal packet tightly. Grill, covered over medium hot heat for 20 minutes or until onions are tender, turning once.

title: curried coconut rice
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat. Stir in curry powder. Add water and broth cubes and bring to a boil. Add rice, coconut milk and raisins. Stir to blend.
Return to boil and then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Put into a serving dish and garnish with fried onions.

title: payday cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan the cake mix, 1 stick margarine and egg.
Press in pan.
Bake for only 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with marshmallows.
Return to oven and melt (not brown).
Take out.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into heavy frying pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes. It turns out good and brown.

title: becky's 13 bean soup
directions: Bring to boil; simmer about 5 hours.
Can be served with sour cream or grated cheese on top.
Ham hock works well instead of ham.

title: fillets elegante
directions: Thaw fish (sole, haddock, halibut or cod).
Separate and arrange in buttered 9-inch dish.
Dash with pepper.
Dot with margarine.
Spread soup over fillets and sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: caramel nut rolls
directions: Roll 1/2 of refrigerator roll recipe, 12 x 8 rectangle.
Brush with 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine; sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar 1- teaspoon ground cinnamon.
Roll lengthwise as for jellyroll; seal edge; cut roll in 1 inch slices.
In 8 x 8-inch pan or round cake pan you are going to bake rolls in, spray good with Pam.
Then melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup of light corn syrup.
Mix well.
Chop up pecans as many as you like sprinkle on top on the mixture in your pan.
Then place your rolls in the pan let rise in warm place till double (35 min.).
Bake at 350° for 20 - 25 min.
For 8 x 10 in pan double your caramel topping recipe.

title: chicken-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Remove pulp from tomatoes to form 1/2 inch tomato shells. Turn shells upside down on paper towels to drain.
Combine chicken, celery, onions, eggs and relish in a medium bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and seasoned salt; add to chicken mixture. Toss lightly until mixed.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fill tomatoes with chicken salad and serve garnished with salad greens.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed plus 1 stick melted margarine and bake.

title: shingled blueberry banana bread
directions: Heat
oven
Drain and rinse blueberries; set aside. Blend
egg,
milk	and
cinnamon
in
a bowl.
Stir in muffin mix just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.) Fold blueberries, bananas
and
nuts	into
batter.
Pour into one large loaf pan or two mini pans.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake for
to 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes
out	clean. Cool
minutes.
Remove from pan(s) and cool completely. Serves 10 to 15.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, 2 sugars and salt.
Add oil.
Take out a scant cup and set aside for topping.
To what is left add buttermilk, soda, baking powder, nutmeg and egg.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: naney's fudge
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in heavy saucepan and cook to 232° (soft-boil). Remove from heat and beat. Add vanilla and pecans. When it thickens, pour out on wax paper and cool. Cut into pieces. Ready to serve. Best if refrigerated for several hours before serving.

title: sweetened whipped cream
directions: Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl with chilled rotary beater or mixer.
Beat until cream stands in peaks when beater is slowly lifted upright.
Beat confectioners sugar and vanilla extract into whipped cream with final few strokes.

title: basic yellow cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.
Frost as desired.
Yield:
One 3-layer cake.

title: heavenly hawaiian cream
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Combine pineapple, reserved syrup, marshmallows and cherries; mix lightly.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Fold in whipped cream.
Sprinkle with almonds and coconut.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry streusel muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat until light.
Add egg and again beat until light.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with orange juice.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into paper-lined muffin tins.
Sprinkle with Crumb Topping.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix butter and graham crackers well.
Reserve 1/4 cup for garnish.
Press firmly on bottom of pan.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour, sour cream and vanilla. Mix well.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites with 1 teaspoon cream of tartar and gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold egg whites thoroughly into cheese mixture and pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle remainder of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Open door; leave for 15 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir while baking (tastes better).
Can add more cheese.

title: low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add egg whites, milk, applesauce and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and let cool.

title: rita's blueberry cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until top is brown and toothpick comes out clean.

title: peas, corn and cream
directions: In large saucepan, combine peas, corn, salt, sugar and nutmeg. Add cream and cover.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are desired tenderness, stirring occasionally.
Thicken by combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into vegetable mixture, bring to boil, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and cook until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat and let set until almost cool.
Whip mixture with prepared Dream Whip.
Serve with pineapple, apple slices, strawberries, bananas, melons and any other fruit.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake sheet
cake.
Punch
holes with a toothpick in the top. Cook pineapple and sugar until sugar is dissolved.	Pour over hot cake.
Mix	pudding
by
package directions and pour over hot cake.
Cool cake, then spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with coconut.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight or a few hours.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add milk and eggs and mix well.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Roll dough thin and cut into circles.
Put 2 circles together with filling in center and pinch outer edge shut.
Bake at 325° until bottoms are slightly brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well and pour into crust.
Chill.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze until ready to use.
Let thaw 1 1/2 hours.
Chop and add ginger ale.
Serves 50 people.

title: pork chop and cream gravy
directions: Fry bacon and pork chops in hot bacon drippings until brown on both sides.
Reduce heat; cover and cook over low heat until chops are tender, about 30 minutes.
Stir flour into fat (oil) and cook until browned.
Pour milk over chops and simmer until gravy is thickened.
Crumble the crisp bacon on top.

title: cranberry fruit nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and lightly flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in orange juice, egg and orange peel, mixing just to moisten.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Wrap and store overnight.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Mix
soup,
Ro-Tel,
broth
and onion together.
Spread layer of
chips
in
baking dish; add 1/2 of the chicken, then pour 1/2 of
soup
mixture over.
Cover with another layer of chips and repeat
until all used.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: glazed carrots(microwave)
directions: Place carrots and water in casserole; cover with tight lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High (100%) for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Allow to stand 5 minutes, then drain.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender in salt water.
Drain and set aside. Mix in a skillet and heat the cheese, soup, 1/2 cup margarine or butter, milk and mayonnaise.
Put this with cabbage; stir, then put in a casserole dish.
Crush crackers; melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix together, then put on top of casserole.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake in 375° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: golden bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Turn off heat. Stir in brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Mix in dry ingredients:
flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and cut.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup with both cheeses until cheese is melted and add shrimp.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: squash walnut bake
directions: *You may substitute 1 egg and 1 cup egg nog for the eggs and cream.

title: southern okra
directions: Combine the first four ingredients. Set aside. Cook okra in boiling water 10 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Heat oil over medium heat and saute onion and pepper until tender. Stir in sugar mixture. Add okra and simmer until heated through stirring as little as possible. Serve with rice if desired.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda, sugar and brown sugar and stir.
Add 2 eggs, 1 cup butter and 1 cup peanut butter.
Batter may be stiff. Spoon on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. In large saucepan, melt butter. Stir in brown sugar. Cool 10 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat after each addition. Stir in flour mixture, nuts and chocolate pieces until well blended. Spread in pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched. Cool and cut into 2-inch squares. Makes 3 dozen.

title: california "chicken" salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in covered bowl.
Add Ranch dressing to taste; stir in pasta.
Cool, covered, overnight or for several hours for best flavor.

title: pizza crust
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix 2 cups Bisquick baking mix and 1/2 cup cold water until soft dough forms.
Roll or pat into 12-inch circle on ungreased cookie sheet; pinch edge, forming 1/2-inch rim.
Top with desired ingredients.
Bake until crust is golden, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix milk, juice, Cool Whip, pecans and pineapple well and pour into 2 pre-baked pie shells. Chill until set.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine the 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine with cracker crumbs and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs on high speed for 4 minutes.
Add sugar and 3/4 cup softened butter or margarine to eggs and beat for 5 minutes.
Spread this over crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Spread drained pineapple over creamed mixture.
Arrange sliced bananas over top of pineapple, cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach on paper towels until dry.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Great with vegetables.

title: venison (or beef) with port, guinness and pickled walnuts(serves 10 people)
directions: Begin this the night before by placing the meat in a large bowl along with the bay leaves and thyme. Pour the Guinness and Port all over it.
Place a plate over the top of the meat and leave in a cool place overnight.

title: girl scout punch
directions: Mix and serve.
Makes enough for 36 (6 ounce).

title: mammy's strawberry pie
directions: Cook the sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add Jell-O. Stir in cut up strawberries.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: layered salad
directions: Shred lettuce and place in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Cover with eggs.
Add salt, pepper and peas.
Sprinkle with Italian dressing.
Add bacon and cheese.
Cover completely with salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Keep in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: maple fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and cream in a deep saucepan.
Stir carefully over low temperature until sugar is dissolved and syrup starts to boil.
Add butter; boil to soft ball stage.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Cool until warm to touch.
Add vanilla and salt; beat until creamy.
Turn into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cut into squares.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Grind all together.
Cook to thicken (takes some time). Put in jars and seal.
Makes about 10 pints.

title: belgium waffles
directions: Mix yeast with lukewarm milk and eggs.
Place dry ingredients in big bowl; make well in center and add egg and yeast mixture. Add melted butter.
With hands, work into a smooth batter.
Cook on a well-greased, hot waffle iron until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Top with whipped cream, flavored and sweetened to taste; serve with fresh, sweetened strawberries.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg with onion. Drain fat. Add taco seasoning, tomato, chillies and tomato sauce. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Combine eggs and Ricotta cheese. In a greased 9 x 13 pan, layer the tortillas, 1/2 of hamburg mixture, tortillas, 1/2 of Ricotta mixture and 2 cups Monterey Jack cheese. Repeat. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in margarine until golden.
Add broccoli as it comes from package. Add soup and cheese and simmer until broccoli is well thawed.
Add cooked rice and almonds.
Simmer a few minutes more.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil ingredients, stirring constantly, until forms a soft ball when tried in cold water.
Remove from fire, beat until thick. Add 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired.

title: cinnamon yummies
directions: Cut crust off of bread.
Roll thin with rolling pin.
Mix cream cheese with 1 tablespoon sugar and spread on each piece of bread.
Roll up bread slice and dip in butter, then cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Cut in half.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These can be made several hours ahead of time, then baked right before serving.
These are great for any occasion.

title: nana cookies(sand tarts)
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add milk and flour with soda. Shape dough into 2-inch roll and chill until hard.
Cut very thin. Dip one side in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Place walnut or peanut half on each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: sunday dinner chicken
directions: Crumble
dried	chipped
beef
into greased baking pan. Mix soup, sour cream and onion powder.	Lay chicken pieces on the dried beef and spread soup mixture over the chicken. Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
(While you are at church.)

title: chocolate pie
directions: Place in saucepan the milk, sugar, flour, cocoa and salt. First add only enough milk to make a paste.
Add egg and mix well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly to keep from scorching. When thick, remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into a baked 8-inch pie shell and let cool completely.

title: molasses icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, eggs and molasses.
Add ginger, soda and salt to flour.
Add pecans.
Make into rolls the desired size of the cookies and place in refrigerator.
Allow to stand overnight or longer, then slice and bake at 350°.

title: old-fashioned carrot cake
directions: Prepare carrot cake mix as directed on box.
Stir in nuts, raisins and pineapple.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost cooled cake with cream cheese frosting.

title: risotto a la milanese
directions: Prepare clear broth and set aside.
Saute onion in butter and oil until golden.
Add rice and stir until rice has absorbed liquid. Pour wine in and stir 2 minutes.
Begin adding broth; stir occasionally until rice is almost cooked.
Add saffron.
Premix cheese and cream and add to risotto.
Turn off heat.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate 12 hours before serving.

title: jack's apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13-inch by 9-inch baking dish.
Combine sugar, 3 tablespoons of the flour, and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl.
Add apples and Jack Daniel's.
Stir to coat apples evenly with sugar mixture.
Pour apples into greased baking dish.
Combine remaining 1 cup flour, salt, and brown sugar in medium mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until topping is golden brown and apples are bubbly.
Serve plain, with ice cream, or caramel sauce.

title: kay's famous baked beans
directions: In bean pot, small roasting pan, etc. mix all of the ingredients.
Add 1/2 the bacon grease.
Bake at 375° for first hour.
Turn to 350° and bake for remaining 2 hours.

title: low-fat cranberry-apple cobbler
directions: Place chopped apple in an 8-inch square pan coated with cooking spray.
Combine cranberry sauce and orange juice, stirring well.
Spoon cranberry sauce mixture evenly over apple.

title: clapshot
directions: Cook the potatoes and turnips in boiling water until tender, then drain well.
Mash together until smooth. Beat in the butter and the snipped chives. Season to taste.
Serve hot.

title: favorite slow cooker chili
directions: Brown
ground chuck; drain fat.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker in order listed.
Stir once to combine.
Cover and cook on low
setting
to
12 hours or high setting 5 to 6 hours.

title: apple harvest gingerbread
directions: Butter and flour 10 inch springform pan.
Line bottom with waxed paper.
Butter and flour paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves, and salt into medium bowl.
Set aside.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Place frozen hash browns in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick oleo and pour on top.
Mix sour cream, soup, cheese, salt and pepper together.
Layer ham on top of hash browns.
Pour mixture on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: moonlight salad dressing
directions: Wash and dry lettuce.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Add croutons and salad dressing right before serving.
If you don't add the bread crumbs, the dressing will stick to the croutons.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Mix potatoes and all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, well.
Heat nonstick skillet on stove.
Melt about 1 tablespoon of butter in skillet on medium heat.
Quickly "dunk" bread slices into egg mixture, then put in skillet.
Cook until lightly browned, turn, cook until lightly brown.
Remove from skillet; spread with butter and top with syrup.
For an added treat, top with your favorite jelly.

title: basic chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and chili powder together. Drain, if necessary. Add kidney beans and tomato sauce, Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with cheese and chopped onions for topping.

title: warmed golden fruit compote
directions: Drain apricot halves.
Combine with all ingredients, except apple.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Stir in apple and heat 5 minutes longer or until apple is heated, but not soft.
Serve warm in individual fruit cups.

title: sweet vidalia onion cheese dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease a baking dish (8-inch) with butter or cooking spray. Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well. Spoon the mixture into the baking dish. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes. Serve warm with the crackers, Fritos or chips of your choice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
Brown roast in shortening in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Drain; discard drippings.
Add tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, onion and garlic to Dutch oven. Combine vinegar and next six ingredients.
Stir well; pour over roast.
Cover; cook 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Remove roast; save liquid in Dutch oven.
Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water until smooth.
Stir.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly and thick.
Spoon over meat; use the rest as gravy.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in lemon juice and fold in cranberry sauce and nuts.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip and mix all well.
Pour into 1-quart mold or 9 x 5 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pan.
(I recommend spraying with Pam first.)
Freeze for 24 hours.
Remove from freezer just before serving.
Unmold and garnish with green grapes, if desired.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions; boil until transparent.
Drain.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Add milk, cracker crumbs and cheese. Stir in onions while hot.
Pour into a 1 1/4-quart casserole dish. Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Will freeze well.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into ungreased cake pan. Makes 1 (9 x 13-inch) or 2 round 9-inch cakes.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate chip toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, stir together flour and brown sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles large crumbs.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of the mixture. Press remaining crumb mixture onto bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: daffodil dip
directions: Mix together and use as a vegetable dip.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Dip fresh strawberries in chocolate bark.
Really pretty for showers and taste oh, so good.

title: banana fruit punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil until sugar dissolves.
Cool. Combine orange juice, bananas and lemonade in blender; process until smooth.
Add pineapple juice and sugar syrup; mix well.
Can put in freezer and store until ready to use.
Thaw 1 hour before serving and spoon into punch bowl.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Mix sour cream, chilies and chicken.
Place small amount in tortilla.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Line in rectangular pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup and enchilada sauce.
Pour over enchiladas. Cover with remainder of cheese.
Bake in greased pan, uncovered, at 350 for 40-45 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together and cream well.
Very good with all kinds of chips.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef in large kettle.
Drain and add onions.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Ladle into bowls.
Add cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel and dice apples.
Mix the rest of ingredients together. Pour into an 8-inch square pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Leave plain or serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; blend well.
In small saucepan, heat water, milk and margarine until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquid and egg to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in 3 to 4 cups of flour until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl.

title: tropical fruit salad snack
directions: Whirl salad and yogurt together until smooth.
Great chilled or in blender.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Place artichoke hearts and mayonnaise in blender or food processor and puree.
Add grated cheese and crushed garlic; puree until well blended.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with Melba toast or cubed baquettes.

title: kathy's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix together all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: josie's bread pudding
directions: Crumble, tear or dice bread.
Place in rectangular pan (about full pan).
Shake cinnamon and nutmeg over dry bread.
Combine and mix well all other ingredients.
Pour over dry bread mixture.

title: vegetable combo
directions: Place broccoli and carrots in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Cover with glass lid.
Microwave for 10 minutes on High. Drain.
Stir in corn, cheese and seasonings.
Sprinkle with onion rings.
Microwave for 5 to 6 minutes or until heated through.
Let stand for 2 minutes before serving.

title: green and white salad
directions: Chop vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise and whipping cream with sugar, salt and pepper.
Add vegetables and let stand overnight.

title: fried sweet plantains
directions: Select very ripe plantains, with a partially black or all black peel and a little soft to the touch.
Remove the peel and slice the plantain obliquely, or in a slant, in about 1-inch slices.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Remove and add peanut butter, oatmeal and flavoring.
Mix in raisins or dates (optional).
Drop by small pieces onto waxed paper.

title: pennsylvania dutch hot potato salad
directions: Cube and boil potatoes.
Combine onion, Velveeta, mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Toss with potatoes to coat.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sliced green olives and sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly and browned on top.

title: marbled cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare chocolate crumb crust.
Stir together margarine and cocoa until smooth.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla, then flour.
Measure 1 1/2 cups batter into medium bowl.
Beat in cocoa mixture.
Spoon half the vanilla batter into prepared pan, then half the chocolate batter.
Repeat, ending with chocolate batter.
With spatula, cut through batters to marble.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Then chill in refrigerator.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients together and marinate chicken for 1 hour. Bake on tinfoil-lined baking sheet at 350°, pouring off fat occasionally.
Cook until as crisp as you like.

title: salted nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and 1 cup butter; blend well. Press mixture in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan or 2 (9-inch) square pans. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Hand mix all together.
Do not blend.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients and then add Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.
(Fruit cocktail may be used in place of pineapple.)

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix well and put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until it gets brown.
Very rich.

title: crab meat pizza appetizer
directions: Prepare crescent rolls as directed in a pizza pan or rectangular baking sheet.
Let cool.
Spread cream cheese onto crust with spatula.
Cover with cocktail sauce, spreading to edge like pizza.
Crumble crab meat on top; chill.

title: simple bread
directions: Measure water into large mixer bowl. Sprinkle yeast over water. Add dry milk, sugar, salt, oil and about 3 1/4 cups flour to make a thick batter. Blend well. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed of mixer. By hand gradually add remaining flour to form a very stiff dough. Toss dough on floured surface until no longer sticky. Knead until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes. Divide in half. Using a rolling pin, shape dough into a 12 x 6-inch rectangle. Roll up tightly, starting with 6-inch side. Seal edges and end. Place seam side down in well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans. Cover. Let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from pans immediately. Brush with butter. Cool on wire rack.

title: chili
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce in heavy skillet. Cook until meat is cooled and onion becomes transparent.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Cook until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add margarine and beat until thick and creamy.
Drop by spoonful onto buttered waxed paper.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: In slow cooker, mix mustard and jelly together.
Slice frankfurters into bite size pieces.
(Or you can get cocktail wieners.)
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Melt butter in a pie dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, cocoa, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add melted butter and then mix until creamy.
Pour back into pie dish.
Cook on High in microwave 2 1/2 minutes.
Turn and cook 2 1/2 minutes longer. Cool and then frost.

title: kapusta deluxe
directions: Drain juice from sauerkraut.
Dice small onion into sauerkraut.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate. Serves 25.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Melt oleo in small pan.
Remove from heat; blend in flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens and boils 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in mayo.
Fold in rest; pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese.
Put hard-boiled eggs, pimentos, onion, salt, mayo and butter in blender and mix well.
Add to grated cheese. Makes a great cracker spread for a party.

title: red velvet cake iii
directions: Mix food coloring with cocoa.
Let stand.
Cream Crisco with sugar; add eggs.
Add colored paste.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk, cake flour (sifted), salt, vinegar and soda.
Mix in by hand. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 layers.

title: easy chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in butter or margarine to lightly brown.
Transfer to baking dish. Mix wine with soup; stir well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover dish and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise or around.
Remove yolks.
Place warm yolks in bowl and mash well.
Mix with butter, mayonnaise, pickles, onion and bell pepper, stirring well.
Pack into whites. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve warm or cold.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in jar with tight lid.
To serve, add 1 tablespoon per coffee mug.
Add hot water and enjoy.

title: green goddess salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill well before serving.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Melt cheese and butter first.
Mix other ingredients with melted cheese (flour and nuts).
Add red pepper and salt to taste. Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Place small balls of mixture on baking pan.
Press crosswise with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water; add 1/2 cup cold water.
Add well drained pineapple; save the juice!
Cover jello with layer of marshmallows.
Let mixture jell.

title: winter fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Using floured fingers, press dough evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Heat soup, then whisk in cream cheese until very smooth. Cool soup.
Pour in gelatin and mix well.
Put in blender the mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish, dill, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add soup mixture and blend together.
Mash salmon, onion and lemon juice until very smooth. Add to other ingredients and blend until smooth.
Pour into oiled mold.
Chill until solid.
Unmold and decorate with cucumber slices and olives. Serve with crackers or cocktail breads.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with chips.

title: cranberry apple walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven.
Grease 8 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan. Combine apples, sugar and oil in medium bowl.
Add egg, mix well. Combine flour, baking powder and soda in separate bowl.
Add apple mixture.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist (do not overmix, do not beat).
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until center springs back when pressed with fingertip.

title: cauliflower quiche
directions: Mix cauliflower, onion and cheese in lightly greased pie tin. Beat remaining ingredients for 15 seconds in blender.
Pour in pie plate and bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the dry ingredients. Cream oleo.
Add NutraSweet, vanilla and egg.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients and beat well. Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in potatoes, sugar, eggs, shortening, salt and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Mix in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Put in greased bowl.
Flip bowl, greased side up; cover tightly. Refrigerate at least 8 hours, 24 hours is best.
Punch down, roll out, shape, set out to rise in warm place.
Let rise until double bulk.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Enough rolls for 1 week.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease baking pan. Melt cocoa and shortening in large saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat. Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When done baking, cut in squares while still hot.
Makes 15 large brownies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine and place in 8 x 8-inch casserole pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This can easily be doubled, but cooking time will be longer.
We have this every Christmas morning!

title: frozen salad
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Place in a 7 x 11-inch dish and freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, butter and salt in a 1-quart dish.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes on high.
Add soda and stir well.

title: spearcarrier
directions: Place 2 to 3 asparagus spears on one end of each ham slice. Roll up to make 6 bundles.
Heat cream cheese and milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring often until smooth.
Blend in sherry, onion salt and nutmeg.
Butter toast; trim crusts and cut each slice diagonally.
Place one ham bundle on each toast point. Spoon 2 tablespoons hot cream cheese sauce over each ham bundle; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes to warm and to brown cheese.
Makes 3 servings.

title: terrific turtles
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper to cool.
Melt Hershey bar in double boiler and dip cooled caramel balls in chocolate.
Lay out to dry on wax paper.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into steaks.
Season both sides with salt and pepper.
Saute onion in oil in skillet.
Add steak; brown on both sides.
Place meat and onion in baking dish.
Add carrots.
Beat tomatoes with electric mixer.
Pour over carrots.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato cheese chowder
directions: Put water and chicken cubes in Dutch oven and boil.
Add vegetables, cover and simmer until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour and cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir cheese sauce into vegetable mixture.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix butter (not melted) and cheese in mixer.
Add dry ingredients.
Add Rice Krispies last.
Make into balls.
Mash with fork.
Cook at 350° (ungreased pan) for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Melt chocolate chips and wax. Shape dough into small balls and dip into chocolate mixture. Place on waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Heat margarine in frying pan.
Add rice and stir until lightly browned (toasted).
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water and pour over rice. Arrange green pepper slices on top of rice.
Cover tightly with foil and put into 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: e-z baked omelet
directions: Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine beaten eggs and the rest of the ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Must set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Other suggested ingredients are sausage, green peppers, green onions, mushrooms and green chilies.
Or create your own combinations and enjoy!

title: easy day casserole
directions: Dilute both cans of soup slightly.
Mix all ingredients and place in greased casserole.
Bake until potatoes are done at 350°. Note:
Do not brown meat.

title: jack's chinese chicken and noodles
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Mix together salt, teriyaki sauce, lemon juice and lemon pepper.
Put chicken into mixture.
Put oil in skillet and add chicken.
Cook half done and remove from skillet.
Pour in more oil.
Add mushrooms, teriyaki sauce, soy sauce, Accent, sugar, wine, hoisin sauce and black pepper.
Put chicken back into skillet and cover and simmer until done.
Thicken by adding 1 tablespoon cornstarch mixed with 1/4 cup water.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, lemon juice and rind, pinch of salt and margarine.
Add hot water and stir thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat until thick, but do not boil. Serve over cake or pudding.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Rinse and dry chicken.
Beat egg and milk together.
Mix potato flakes, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.

title: safety glue
directions: You will need baby food jars.

title: broiled lamb chops
directions: In a large skillet place lamb chops and mix in all ingredients.
Cook on medium-high for 1 hour, then let simmer for 30 minutes or until desired tenderness.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slightly beat eggs in a mixing bowl. Mix Bisquick, sugar, oil and yogurt in a mixing bowl; stir. Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full (muffin cups should be lined or lightly greased).
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Slice celery, onion, mushrooms, green onions and water chestnuts.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet.
Brown meat and push to side of pan.
Add all vegetables except spinach.
Stir in remaining ingredients and let cook 5 minutes.
Add spinach, cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Serve with boiled rice.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Whip the whipping cream; fold in mayonnaise and horseradish. Great with roast beef.

title: three cheese potatoes
directions: Grate cheeses.
Parboil potatoes for approximately 10 to 15 minutes, then grate them.
Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together; add 2 eggs and milk. Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Add oats and vanilla and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased tins.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 1 1/2-quart dish for 1/2 hour at 350° or until center is thick.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
This pie has the look of a pecan pie and its consistency, too.
You mix it, cook it and eat it!
So simple, its too good to be true.

title: party cheese ball
directions: In large bowl beat cheeses at medium speed; mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Mix well. Chill several hours or overnight.
Shape into ball, roll in pecans and serve.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy; blend in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add combined flour, soda and salt. Mix well.
Stir in candies and nuts.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet about 3 inches apart. Press 3 to 4 additional candies into each cookie, if desired. Bake at 350°.

title: frosted orange jello
directions: Mix together and let set.

title: butterscotch dip for apples
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a very heavy boiler until smooth and well blended.

title: dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Will be soupy.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex until done at 350°.
Serve with chicken or turkey.

title: chocolate pecan shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Combine flour and salt in food processor, do pecans until fine not powdery.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat butter and sugar.
Reduce to slower speed, beat in flour mixture. Roll into tablespoon ball.
Put onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Flatten about 2 inches around.
Bake 30 minutes. Melt chocolate in 250° oven.
Dip half cookie in melted chocolate or pour melted chocolate on cookie.

title: mock veal cutlets
directions: Combine eggs, turkey, garlic, cheese, nutmeg, salt and pepper and enough breadcrumbs to shape meat into patties.
Brown patties in butter until well browned.
Remove and keep warm.
Add flour to butter in pan and cook, making paste.
Add juice of lemon.
Stir. Now add enough chicken broth to make gravy consistency and serve over cutlets.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Melt butter and margarine and pour over mixture.
Stir; leave overnight.
Next day, stuff clam shells and bake at 375° until done.

title: chocolate marshmallow cream
directions: Blend sugar, gelatin, milk, and chocolate thoroughly in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to a boil. Place pan in cold water, cool until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon. Stir in marshmallows and nuts.Fold in egg whites and whipped cream. Chill 4 hrs. 8 servings.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake mix according to package direction in 13 x9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into cubes.
Combine chocolate pudding with milk and Kahlua.
Layer 1/2 of cake cubes in glass bowl.
Spread with 1/2 of pudding mixture, then 1/2 of whipped cream.
Top with 1/2 of candy.
Repeat layers, ending with candy.
Chill overnight.

title: zucchini and corn
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, or until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: pear, endive and pecan salad
directions: Arrange greens on salad plates.
Top with sliced pears, toasted pecans and 2 ounces peppercorn dressing.
Yields 4 servings.

title: bavarian delight(pork fillets in natural gravy)
directions: Cut pork fillets in half so you end up with 8 pieces.
Dip fillets in flour one side only.
Melt the butter in a frying pan; let pan get hot and add pork fillets with flour side down.
Let brown until they are dark brown, then turn fillets over and brown other side.
Sprinkle salt onto fillets and into the pan.
Spread garlic onto fillets and let some garlic drop into the pan as well. When garlic starts browning, add enough water to cover the fillets halfway.
Turn heat down, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
While fillets are simmering, boil noodles and prepare vegetables.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Add onions and saute 3 minutes. Add meat, vegetables (drained), tomato soup.
Stir over low heat until well mixed and thoroughly heated.
Season to taste.
Pour mixture into greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Cover with mashed potatoes and bake at 400° about 15 minutes until potatoes are light brown. 6 servings.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Combine beef, egg white, onions, crumbs, milk, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Shape into four oval patties.
Fry in skillet with a small amount of oil 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove and keep warm. Add gravy, mushrooms and water to skillet.
Heat and serve over patties and noodles.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable spray.
Place chicken pieces and broccoli on the bottom of the pan.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Pour this mixture on top of chicken-broccoli mixture. Mix stuffing mix and margarine together and sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake in a 350° oven
for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 5 servings.

title: purple cow shakes
directions: Pour juice and milk into blender.
Scoop in the vanilla ice cream.
Cover and blend for 30 seconds.
Serve.
If you do not have your blender handy, just place in a 2-quart jar and shake.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chickens or pressure for 15 minutes.
Saute onion in butter; add green chilies.
Add soups, milk and broth; warm thoroughly.
Separate chicken from bones.
Moisten tortillas in leftover broth and line casserole dishes.
Layer:
meat, soup mixture and cheese.
Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes two 9 x 13-inch dishes full.
Freezes well.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup flour with the dates and nuts. Set aside.

Blend together the egg, milk, oil, sugar and marmalade or jam. Sift the remaining flour, salt and baking powder into the bowl with the liquid mixture and mix quickly, only enough to moisten the flour. Add dates and nuts and fold in.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Test with toothpick.
Cool for 30 minutes on rack before turning out of pan. Cool thoroughly before wrapping to store.
Freezes very well.

title: peppered deer steak
directions: Saute steaks in soy sauce, garlic and oil for at least 1 hour. Place in skillet with onions, peppers and celery.
Cook on high and brown, then simmer with remaining ingredients until done. Pour over rice.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: In a small bowl, combine cheese and margarine until well blended.
Spread 1/4 of mixture on 1 ham slice.
Repeat with remaining cheese mixture and ham slice.
Roll up from short sides; chill for several hours or wrap and freeze, if desired.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat 1/2 cup sugar into the egg yolks.
Add salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats the spoon.
Cool.

title: mama's clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until almost crisp.
Remove and add onions; cook 5 minutes.
Crumble bacon.
Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Add all ingredients except clams.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add clams and heat 3 minutes.

title: raw vegetable dip(the best)
directions: Mix and chill.	Serve
with
raw
vegetables.
(This is the best recipe for a relish tray that you can make.)

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles as directed on package.
Rinse and drain.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix soda into the boiling water and cool mixture.
Cream together the remaining ingredients.
Add the water and soda mixture.
Bake in papered muffin tins at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Mixture will keep in the refrigerator for up to one week.

title: cuchin cake
directions: Cut cake mix and butter together in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool well.
Beat sour cream, eggs and sugar together.
Pour over cake.
Bake again at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Pour both fillings over half of cake and serve.

title: light tiramisu
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat Egg Beaters and sugar until thick (about 1 minute).
Place in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add cheeses and beat well.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture; set aside.

title: ranch chicken breasts with salsa
directions: Mix dressings and pepper.
Spread dressing mixture over chicken; cover. Refrigerate at least 20 minutes to marinate.
Heat grill.
Remove chicken from marinade; place on grill over medium coals.
Grill, covered, 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until cooked through.
Serve with salsa.

title: total catfish
directions: Preheat
oven
Wash and dry fillets
and
cut into serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper in egg white and coat
with Total cornflake crumbs.
Arrange in
a
single layer in a lightly oiled shallow baking dish.
Bake
for about 30 minutes or until it looks brown and crispy.
This recipe is very "heart healthy!"

title: french onion soup
directions: In heavy bottomed, 4-quart covered pot, melt butter and oil. Add onions.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Stir in salt and sugar.
Cook over moderate heat for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring frequently, until onions are deep golden brown.
Sprinkle in flour and stir over low heat for several minutes to cook flour. In a separate pot, bring broth to a boil.
Remove soup pot from heat and add boiling liquid, wine and seasonings.
Simmer, partially covered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in cognac.
Pour in soup tureen or individual ovenproof bowls. Stir in some cheese and top with toasted French bread.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Place bowls on cookie sheet and cover with the rest of the cheese.
Bake 15 minutes in a 325° oven and serve immediately.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush wafers and add butter.
Mix well. Press into a 9-inch pie plate. Cover with softened coffee ice cream. Top with cold fudge.
(Tip:
It helps to place fudge sauce in the freezer for awhile to make the spreading easier.) Store Mud Pie in the freezer for approximately 10 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli until undercooked stage; drain well.
Mix cut broccoli with the remaining ingredients.
Stir thoroughly and refrigerate overnight before serving.
Salad will keep 3 days refrigerated.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil water and margarine together; let cool.
Put flour in; stir until smooth.
Put in eggs; beat hard.
Place in refrigerator; let stand overnight.
Drop from a teaspoon in small balls; shape with fingers.
Bake at 400° until brown, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix sugars and flour. Beat eggs, milk, vanilla and butter, then add in sugars and flour. Fold in nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 to 50 minutes, until firm and golden brown.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs and beat until smooth and creamy.
Add milk and cook slowly, stirring constantly, so it won't scorch.
When thick and smooth, remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: no-citron fruit cake
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients gently for 3 minutes.
Cool in a large bowl.
Beat in eggs; add orange juice, cherries and nuts.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Add gradually to fruit mixture.
Makes three 7 x 3-inch pans or two 2 1/2 x 5-inch pans.
Bake in slow oven at 275° for approximately 1 hour, depending on pans used.

title: baby onions with curried cream sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour and stir for 3 to 4 minutes on medium heat.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add salt and pepper to taste, then add the curry powder.
Add well drained onions.
Stir and heat through.

title: hummos(arabic)
directions: Heat beans.
Drain.
Put garlic, hot pepper, parsley, lemon juice and tahini in blender or food processor and chop.
Add beans and salt.
Blend to fine consistency.
Reserve a few whole beans for garnish.
Add a little water if too thick.
Spread in large, flat plate.
Make a mound between center and edge of plate in hummos for olive oil.
Garnish with leftover whole chickpeas and sprigs of parsley.
Serve with warm pita bread to be dunked into food.
Serves about 4.

title: refreshing drink
directions: Combine thawed orange juice and lemonade.
Add ice.
Then add the ginger ale to the mixture and enjoy!

title: baked stuffed haddock
directions: Crumble crackers in a bowl.
Cook onions in margarine on medium-low heat. (Don't burn margarine.)
Cook until soft, 5 to 7 minutes.
Pour into crumbled crackers.
Add Parmesan cheese.

title: fried and baked chicken
directions: Put flour in plastic bag.
Drop chicken pieces in; shake.
Put in hot skillet with a little oil or Crisco.
Fry each piece until brown.
Put a cake cooling rack on cookie sheet.
Place chicken on rack.
Put in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water and undiluted lemonade concentrate in saucepan.
Place over low heat.
Stir constantly until gelatin dissolves, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until completely cooled.
Pour chilled evaporated milk into chilled mixing bowl; beat at high speed of mixer until stiff, about 5 minutes.
Fold in cooled gelatin mixture.
Add a few drops of food coloring to make pink.
Put in crust.
Chill for about 2 hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix everything together.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes, then pour in dish.
Make a pan of biscuits.
Let cool.
Cut in half and put on top of pie.

title: mexican king ranch casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion.
Blend the last 4 ingredients. Spray baking dish with Pam and layer tortillas, chicken, onion, pepper and soup mixed with tomatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flakes.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick 'n easy salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon or tuna; set aside 2 tablespoons of the juice. In a medium mixing bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky. Stir in the flour.
Add baking powder to salmon or tuna juice. Stir into salmon mixture.
Form into small patties and fry until golden brown (about 5 minutes) in hot Crisco.
Serve with tartar sauce or Caesar salad dressing.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak black beans overnight; drain and add water and olive oil and after a few minutes, add pureed tomatoes, stewed tomatoes, salt, cayenne, oregano, cinnamon, cumin powder, basil and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil, then lower fire to a simmer until done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: nutty fruit medley
directions: In large bowl, combine apples, grapes, banana and walnuts. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt; pour over fruit mixture and toss gently to coat. Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Cut chicken in pieces and fry in oil until a delicate brown. Remove from pan.
Add the unwashed, uncooked rice to the oil in the pan and fry until golden, stirring frequently.
Add onion, garlic, tomato puree and boiling water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the browned chicken and let simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Do not remove.
Cover.
It must steam thoroughly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter in a heavy pan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Pour immediately over popped corn.
Mix lightly but well.
Place in a large roaster pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour. Stir once while baking.
Pour on waxed paper and separate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix all together and chill.

title: onion casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in greased baking dish.
Top with potato chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican spaghetti sauce
directions: In large non-stick skillet, cook beef and onions over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Using a slotted spoon, remove beef mixture to several layers of white paper towels. Let stand for 1 minute. Blot top with of beef with additional white paper towels. Transfer beef mixture to fine mesh strainer over a 1 1/2 quart bowl. Pour hot water over beef. Drain for 5 minutes. In large saucepan, combine spaghetti sauce, beans, tomatoes, corn, salsa, chiles, chili powder, salt and pepper. Stir in beef mixture. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, simmer uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over spaghetti.

title: meat balls and sauce
directions: Mix together.
Make into small balls.
Bake on broiler pan rack for drainage of excess fat for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
In separate bowl, beat eggs,
milk
and soda.
Sift together remaining ingredients, adding
alternately with liquid to the egg mixture; mix well. Drop
onto greased cookie sheet and add a Muscat raisin in center of each.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and zucchini parmesan
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon Parmesan and flour.
Toss zucchini and chicken pieces in it, then place in microwave-safe casserole. Cover and cook on High for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Combine 1 tablespoon Parmesan and crumbs.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Cover with paper towel and cook 2 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce over crumbs and sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Cook, uncovered, about 2 minutes until chicken is done and cheese is melted.
Serve with vermicelli and remaining sauce.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend ingredients and pat into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: whole wheat orange bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine oil, milk and dry ingredients. Mix until dry ingredients are moist.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Sprinkle with a mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon if desired.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: classic chocolate truffles
directions: Place cream in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly with wooden spoon.
As soon as cream reaches boiling point, remove from
heat, add the chopped chocolate and cover the pan.
Leave covered for three minutes to allow chocolate to melt.
Stir the mixture until perfectly blended and smooth.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes to cool and stiffen.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper lined cookie sheet and refrigerate for one hour or until firm.
Form into balls and dip into chocolate.

title: layered pudding dessert
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and bake in a 375° oven until brown.
Cool.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Dissolve the jello in boiling water.
Mix the eggs and cake mix and add to jello mix.
Grease 1 large or 2 small loaf pans. Line with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn onto cake plate.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie roll onto greased pizza pan.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.
Let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together until smooth.
Spread on cooled sugar cookie. Arrange fruits on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: coconut drink(dose for 500 grs.)
directions: Mix together the milk, coconut milk and nutmeg.
Pour the mixture in cold glasses.
(Put them in the fridge for 1/2 hour.) Beat the whipping cream until it becomes soft and cover the upper part of the glasses.
Put the chopped coconut on the top.
When you mix the two different kinds of milk, you can add crushed ice.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chips.
Pour over cereal; toss to coat.
Pour powdered sugar into a large grocery bag.
Put coated cereal into bag and shake gently.
Pour into dish to serve.

title: red top salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in hot water and pour on top of whipping cream.
Let set until firm.

title: carrot cupcakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Put all remaining ingredients into blender container.
Cover and process 3 cycles at grind or until carrots are chopped coarsely. Stir carrot mixture into dry ingredients until just moistened.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions.
Heat oil and saute garlic and onions until tender. Add marinara, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer over low heat 1 hour.
Saute sausage until brown. Discard fat.
Mix Ricotta and diced Mozzarella cheese together in a bowl. Spread 1/2 cup sauce on bottom of baking pan.
Arrange noodles with layers of cheese mixture, Parmesan cheese, tomato sauce and meat.
Repeat process, ending with layer of noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons Parmesan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
(Ground beef can substitute for sausage.)

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Melt butter in skillet and brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Stir in flour and tomato sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Mix together sour cream, cottage cheese, salt and onions.
Add to meat mixture and cool a little.
Layer noodles and meat mixture in casserole dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Pour rice into baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Mix soups together with 3 cans of water and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375°
for 2 hours.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in flour and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add syrup, eggs, vanilla and flour. Mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: pepper pot soup
directions: Cook all the meat, partially covered, in 2 quarts water over low heat for about 1 hour, skimming the surface occasionally.
Add okra, green pepper, spinach and scallions and simmer for 15 minutes. Add yams, thyme, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until yams are cooked, about 30 minutes.
If too thick, add more water. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: depression cake
directions: Boil raisins and add water to liquid to make 1 cup.
Cream sugar, shortening and syrup.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins and liquid and water.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until it springs back when cake is touched lightly.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients until well mixed.
Then beat 1 egg, 1 tbsp vinegar and 1/2 cup water and add all at once to flour mixture and mix to consistency for rolling.
(This can be stored in plastic bag in refrigerator for later use if not all used at once.)

title: apricot lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done in tube pan or loaf pan.

title: spiced pumpkin fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, butter, milk, pumpkin and spice.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches 234° farenheit on candy thermometer, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in butterscotch morsels.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Quickly pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, spreading just until even.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Store, tightly wrapped, in refrigerator.
Yield: 3 pounds of candy.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix soup with two cans of water in large casserole dish; quarter potatoes.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Place potatoes in soup.
Lightly brown the pork.
Add to the mixture.
Peel onions and slice thinly.
Place slices over the meat.
Bake at 400° for one hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Spray 8 1/2 x 11 inch pan with cooking spray or oil pan. Cut peeled apple into 8 sections. Wrap each slice with a crescent roll. Melt butter, sugar and cinnamon. Place wrapped apples in baking dish. Spoon sauce over each wrapped dumpling. Pour Mountain Dew around sides of pan. (Do not pour directly over dumplings.) Bake uncovered for 20 minutes in preheated 350 degree oven.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer chicken stock, onion and broccoli 15 minutes.
Put into a bowl.
In same saucepan, combine milk, butter and flour until thick.
Combine stock, broccoli and onion mixture with milk mixture.
Heat until thickened.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Line a 15 x 9 x 1-inch pan with waxed paper.
Pour into paper and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll up cake and towel.
Let cool completely.
Then unroll and add filling and roll again. Chill and cut.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and half of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Decorate.

title: lamb chops with rosemary mustard sauce
directions: Saute lamb chops in olive oil and garlic. Turn several times, browning on both sides.
Add the wine and cover for 5 minutes. Remove lid and cook for 5 minutes longer.
Add rosemary, mustard and, if needed, a splash more wine.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Heat in oven until melted.
Combine milk, flour, sugar and baking powder in a bowl.
Pour into melted margarine; do not stir. Arrange fruit on top; do not stir.
Bake for 40 minutes or until light brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: orange cooler
directions: Bake cake according to box, in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool cake. Make pudding as directed on box. Cover cake with pudding. Sprinkle pineapple on top. Frost with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients in medium pan, stir to dissolve sugar.
Bring to almost boiling.
Let cool and pour over combined vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fried catfish
directions: Cut fillets into serving size (4 ounces).
Soak fish in milk for 1 hour.
Mix flour, corn meal, salt, pepper and crab-shrimp seasoning together.
Drain fish and dredge in corn meal mix.
Deep fry in 375° oil, a few pieces at a time, until golden brown.
Keep pieces warm in 200° oven until all done.

title: sweet corn muffins
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and separately mix the flour mixture and the milk mixture together.
Grease muffin tins and fill each cup 1/2 full of batter.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes or until golden brown at 450°.

title: roman holiday dish
directions: Saute onion in melted Crisco.
Add meat and seasonings; cook 5 minutes.
Place a layer of spaghetti in baking dish; add meat, another layer of spaghetti, repeating until all ingredients are used.
Pour in tomatoes, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake, covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and continue to bake for an additional 10 minutes to brown cheese.

title: bride's salad
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar with hot water and stir until dissolved. Set aside to chill just until syrupy. Fold in remaining ingredients adding whipped cream last. Chill for several hours.

title: tacos
directions: Brown beef and drain fat off.
Add onion, salt and chili powder.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and beans.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Heat tortillas in very little oil in skillet about a couple of seconds
on one side, then the other side.
Put some of mixture and side dishes in tortillas and serve.

title: ham glaze
directions: Score ham; put whole cloves in each score.
Mix all ingredients together to make paste.
Every 1/2 hour to one hour baste ham until done.
Bake at 350°.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour and Cajun spice together.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Cook at 250° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Cover with foil while cooking.
Uncover for last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: easy ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; serve immediately or chill several hours.

title: sour cream cranberry salad
directions: Mix jellied cranberry sauce and 1 cup hot water in blender; mix until liquid. Dissolve both packages of gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Add cranberry mixture and pecans to gelatin. Put 1/2 of mixture in 8-inch dish; chill in freezer until firm. Spread sour cream over top of chilled mixture. Add second half of gelatin mixture over sour cream and refrigerate.

title: coal miner's cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in a Baggie.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt butter and pour over cookies.
Mix milk, pudding and cream cheese.
Pour over cookies.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding mixture. Crush a few cookies and sprinkle on top for decoration or use chocolate sprinkles.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight or 6 to 8 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook sausage and onion together.
Then mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies(from epcot center walt disney world)
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, salt, baking powder, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy.
Fold in cake flour.
Add chocolate chips, stirring just enough to mix evenly.
Wrap cookie dough in plastic wrap, forming two 2-inch rolls of dough. Refrigerate and chill thoroughly.

title: olive garden fettucine alfredo
directions: In large saucepan, combine cream cheese, Parmesan, butter and milk, stirring constantly, until smooth. Toss pasta lightly with sauce, coating well. Leftovers freeze well.

title: hot dog roll-ups
directions: Butter bread (1 slice at a time), place cheese on opposite side and hot dog, fold over, use toothpick to hold together.
Place on cooking pan.
Bake at 325° until bread is brown.

title: marinated oysters
directions: Simmer oysters in large pot in own juices until edges curl but oysters are still very plump, approximately 10 minutes.
Drain in colander and cool.
Check for shell pieces, but do not rinse. Place oysters in glass dish in single layer.
Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Pour over oysters.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours covered with plastic wrap.
Turn oysters at least twice.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Mix crumbs, margarine, sugars and milk together in pan.
Bring to boil; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put 1 layer of crackers in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of the boiled mixture on top.
Put a second layer of crackers and top with remaining boiled mixture.
Top with 1 more layer of crackers.
Melt together the chips and peanut butter.
Spread over top of crackers. Cool and cut.

title: party nuts
directions: Cream egg white and sugar; stir in pecans until well covered. Spread on cookie sheet and bake 30 minutes at 275°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each.
Alternate flour, cocoa and baking powder mixture with milk to the batter mixture.
Add vanilla; bake.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: stew
directions: Flour and brown stew meat in skillet with oil.
Put browned meat in kettle and add water, salt and pepper.
Cook about 1 hour. Add carrots and continue cooking about 45 minutes.
Add celery, potatoes and onions.
If necessary, add enough water to cover vegetables.
Simmer until done.

title: vegetable lovers' chili
directions: In 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours or until chili is desired consistency.
Remove bay leaf. Sprinkle about 2 tablespoons cheese atop each serving.
Serves 10.

title: oven omelette
directions: Cook sausage and/or fry bacon.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Set in refrigerator overnight in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Add nuts.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.
These cookies are moist and do not spread out much on the cookie sheet.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Stir in milk, stirring constantly until thick, about 15 minutes. Stir in beaten egg yolks gradually.
Check in 5 more minutes. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Pour over wafers and banana layer.

title: lumpy pie
directions: Mix and press into pie pan. Bake this shell at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes until light golden brown.

title: green chili corn
directions: Make a white sauce of milk and flour, beating in eggs to thicken.
When thickened, stir in corn.
Butter a 4-quart casserole.
Put about 1/3 of the corn mixture in bottom.
Top with a layer of green chilies, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat until corn is gone. Top off with cheese. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sunday yeast rolls
directions: Work flour and Crisco together with fingers until blended. Dissolve yeast, salt and sugar in water.
Pour into flour mixture. Work as you would biscuit dough.
Shape into small balls and put into greased muffin tins, 3 dough balls to a muffin.
Cover and let rise one hour in warm place.
Top with melted butter.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all but last 3 items in a bowl; pour into a meat loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour over it the tomato sauce; add the cut up green pepper.
Sprinkle with more Romano.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High for 18 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes and frozen corn.

title: grandma bonnie's potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Then cook until done.
Let cool.
Dice onion, celery and pimentos.
Add to cooked potatoes.

title: babysitters casserole
directions: Combine soup, oregano, salt and onion in saucepan.
Drain beans; reserve liquid.
Add enough water to bean liquid to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir liquid into soup mixture; add tuna.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Add rice, stirring well.
Remove from heat.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange beans around edge of casserole and pimento in center; cover.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: vegetable garden dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Yield: 2 cups, 45 calories per tablespoon.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix sour cream, cottage cheese and marshmallows.
Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Add to mixture. Put in covered dish and refrigerate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Put on stove and stir constantly until boils. When boils, remove immediately.
Cool and store in containers.

title: club sauce(similar to chili sauce)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in large pot.
Boil for 1 1/2 hours, then add the sweet peppers and red hot peppers.
Boil 15 minutes.
Can or bottle.

title: taco corn bread
directions: Combine beef, egg, onion, tomato sauce and taco seasoning. Brown in skillet until done.
Prepare corn meal muffin mix according to package.
Combine meat on bottom layer and then add corn and cheese to muffin mix.
Pour muffin mix over meat mixture. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: elegant green beans
directions: Combine green beans, cream of mushroom soup, milk, 1/2 can of onions and salt and pepper in casserole dish.
Mix together thoroughly.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove; sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Cook 15 minutes longer and remove.
Serves about 6 to 8.

title: daddy's cajun potato soup
directions: Pare and dice potatoes, add onion, water and salt.
Boil until tender.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place milk, cocoa, salt, vanilla and sugar into bowl and put stick of butter in middle of mixture.
Cook in microwave for 3 minutes and remove.
Stir in pecans and pour into buttered dish. Cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients; mix well.
Combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour butter into two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves.
